(373, 1, '2011-09-08 16:42:16', '2011-09-08 16:42:16', '<p>The global technology market is the fastest moving sector in the world, with businesses of all sizes fighting to attract and nurture the talent they need to become the market leaders of the future.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur Technology team offers a wealth and breadth of expertise unmatched in our industry: seasoned recruitment professionals and specialists with priceless ‘&#39;client-side’&#39; experience. Utilising state-of-the-art recruitment tools and processes, the team covers a wide range of sub-sectors – software, hardware, telecommunications, networking, technology consulting, professional services and media services – recruiting across all roles and functions in each. The team frequently helps businesses to recruit senior executives, including regional vice presidents, managing directors and IT directors and into:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operations</li>\r\n<li>Marketing</li>\r\n<li>HR</li>\r\n<li>Sales</li>\r\n<li>Finance</li>\r\n<li>Technology</li>\r\n<li>Procurement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our clients range from blue-chip multinationals through to SMEs or small start-ups and include some of the best-known technology brands in the world today. They choose us because they know we can consistently deliver the very best talent.</p>\r\n', 'Technology', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'technology', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:26:28', '2011-10-17 15:26:28', '', 265, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?page_id=373', 2, 'page', '', 0),
(1726, 6, '2011-10-17 15:10:37', '2011-10-17 15:10:37', 'LOS ANGELES, October 10, 2011 - Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today\r\nannounced the appointment of Jaishankar (Jai) Adhinarayanan as VP, Global Service\r\nManagement Centers.\r\nMr. Jaishankar joins Futurestep with an incredible depth of experience in the management of\r\nservice organizations, with a concentration on start-ups and process improvement of HRO, BPO\r\nand ITES operations. Most recently, he was the General Manager (Operations/Finance) of\r\nRisesmart in India, where he was heading service delivery for the India Center.\r\nPrevious roles include Transformation Leader and Delivery Project Executive at IBM, driving\r\ntransition, delivery and process redesign within their HRO Operations using lean six sigma\r\npractices, and he has also worked in related roles for Exult and ACS.\r\nMr. Jaishankar has spent time working in EMEA, the U.S. and Asia and is a Certified Six Sigma\r\nMaster Black Belt.\r\n“Our Service Management Centers (SMCs) around the world are a critical and valued part of the\r\nFuturestep infrastructure. The capabilities and expertise centered in our SMCs allow us to\r\nprovide sophisticated and efficient recruitment solutions that deliver real impact to our clients\r\naround the world. Today, we have six global SMCs; in Houston, Shanghai, Bangalore, Warsaw,\r\nAuckland, and Sydney and are intending to open a seventh in 2012 in Buenos Aires. Jai’s\r\nappointment and deep expertise will undoubtedly further enhance the breadth and quality of\r\nservices provided by our SMCs. I am delighted he has chosen to join the Futurestep team,”\r\nsaid Futurestep’s Chief Executive Officer Byrne Mulrooney.\r\nMr. Jaishankar said, “It gives me great pleasure to be a part of the Futurestep family. This is a\r\ngreat opportunity to bring together cutting-edge technology and standardized global operations\r\nwith the expertise of the Futurestep team. I am looking forward to further developing our\r\ncapabilities to provide transformational solutions to our clients.”\r\n\r\nAbout Futurestep\r\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions; offering fully\r\ncustomized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs.\r\nOur clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure, proprietary\r\ncompetency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to\r\nmeasure and optimize business impact.\r\nAs a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements; from RPO\r\nand project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class\r\ncapability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify,\r\nattract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit\r\n<a href="http://www.futurestep.com">www.futurestep.com</a>.\r\n\r\nAbout Korn/Ferry International\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the\r\nMiddle East and Africa, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based in Los\r\nAngeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and\r\nreward their talent. Visit <a href="http://www.kornferry.com/">http://www.kornferry.com</a> for more information on the Korn/Ferry\r\nInternational family of companies, and <a href="http://www.kornferryinstitute.com/">http://www.kornferryinstitute.com</a> for thought leadership,\r\nintellectual property and research.', 'FUTURESTEP APPOINTS JAI ADHINARAYANAN TO RUN GLOBAL', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1720-revision-3', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:10:37', '2011-10-17 15:10:37', '', 1720, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
