(427, 1, '2010-02-04 10:30:27', '2010-02-04 10:30:27', 'LOS ANGELES, February 4, 2010 -- Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry Company (NYSE: KFY), today announced that it has commenced work with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), providing strategic talent acquisition solutions to help the agency address its continuing talent needs. The relationship is based on a GSA contract awarded in 2009.\r\nFuturestep‚Äôs support for the SEC will include both recruitment and strategic services, with a focus on the implementation of best-practice talent acquisition processes and expert support related to workforce planning, employment branding and talent technology strategy. Key goals of the effort will be to expand and support the Commission‚Äôs capabilities for identifying, attracting and retaining talent in areas such as accounting, law, management, IT, industry specialists and financial professionals. Futurestep will provide recruitment, project management and consulting services, with an onsite team structured to change based on the agency‚Äôs talent needs. The solution and program is structured to support the SEC‚Äôs growth and transformational strategy, including a one year contract with three additional renewable years and a fifth year option.\r\n‚ÄúWe understand the importance of talent in driving the success of the SEC,‚Äù said Robert McNabb, Executive Vice President, Korn/Ferry International and Chief Executive Officer, Futurestep. ‚ÄúFuturestep has provided essential support in helping the Commission secure critical talent in the past. We look forward to continuing that relationship, leveraging our strategic solutions to help the agency enhance its ability to compete for the vital talent it needs, both today and in the future.‚Äù\r\nAbout Futurestep Futurestep is a Korn/Ferry Company and a leading global talent acquisition solutions provider, helping companies build and implement strategies for improving their talent acquisition operations. Key areas of focus include 