(459, 1, '2010-12-09 11:37:24', '2010-12-09 11:37:24', 'Dedicated leadership underscores growing demand for Futurestep and Newman Group consulting services in the region.\r\nLOS ANGELES, December 9, 2010 ‚ÄìFuturestep, a Korn/Ferry company today announced that Kevin Copithorne has joined the organization as its Consulting Services Practice Manager in Canada. The addition of dedicated consulting services leadership in Canada reflects the growing presence of Futurestep and its Newman Group division as providers of talent management consulting services in the region.\r\nFuturestep‚Äôs Canadian consulting services solutions draw on the global talent management expertise of Korn/Ferry International and reflect the continued growth and success of its U.S.-based consulting organization, The Newman Group. The company‚Äôs consulting services address all facets of talent management, including workforce planning, talent acquisition strategy, integrated talent management, talent management technology selection and implementation, and systems administration and support.\r\nWith more than 15 years of experience in the human capital management field, Mr.Copithorne has consulted internationally to more than 45 midi-sized to Fortune 500 companies on both a regional and global basis. He has published a number of articles and been a sought-after presenter and facilitator on broad talent management issues. In his role, Mr. Copithorne will oversee the growth of talent management consulting as part of Futurestep‚Äôs suite of services in Canada, complementing the company‚Äôs Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), Project-based Recruitment and Mid-level Recruitment services.\r\n‚ÄúDrawing on the global experience and reputation of Korn/Ferry International, The Newman Group and Futurestep have a tremendous presence in North America‚Äôs market for talent acquisition and talent management consulting services,‚Äù said Kelly Cartwright, General Manager, The Newman Group. ‚ÄúThrough Kevin‚Äôs leadership, we look forward to providing our Canadian clients with best-practice expertise and support in all areas of talent management.‚Äù\r\nSince its acquisition by Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry Company (NYSE: KFY) in 2008, The Newman Group has continued to grow its reputation as a leading provider of talent management strategy and expertise for today‚Äôs Fortune 1000 companies.', 'KEVIN COPITHORNE JOINS FUTURESTEP TO LEAD GROWTH OF CONSULTING SERVICES BUSINESS IN CANADA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kevin-copithorne-joins-futurestep-to-lead-growth-of-consulting-services-business-in-canada', '', '', '2011-09-12 11:38:41', '2011-09-12 11:38:41', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=459', 0, 'press', '', 0),
