ompany like yours?</strong>\r\nTo give you a rough idea we save a minimum 10 per cent on a company‚Äôs recruitment process.\r\n<strong>This is a time when many of your clients may have frozen hiring. What role does your company play in such times?</strong>\r\nThere are three major things that we do apart from recruiting: employment brand-building, maintaining an ‚Äúapplicant tracking system‚Äù as part of the recruitment management process, and this is the hardest part of HR today, and lastly, workforce planning, that is, building a database of quality people. Workforce planning is key to the success of an RPO company. Along with this we do talent acquisition assessment. So in a nutshell, we help companies understand if their recruitment process works.\r\n<strong>What are some of the challenges that the RPO model can face in India?</strong>\r\nEmployment brand-building is one of the major challenges for our clients here. The employment brand of a company augments its ability to attract talent. There are many companies whose employment brand doesn‚Äôt help them and, in fact, it works to their competitor‚Äôs advantage. So we help companies look at the market place and competitors, and design a sound employment brand strategy that helps improve the companies‚Äô recruitment brand and attract the sort of talent they need. Additionally, the RPO model is not for everybody. It is more for an enlightened company that is willing to change.', '‚ÄòRPO is for the enlightened‚Äô', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '475-revision-2', '', '', '2011-09-12 13:59:53', '2011-09-12 13:59:53', '', 475, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
