(1734, 6, '2011-10-17 15:17:13', '2011-10-17 15:17:13', 'LOS ANGELES, October 10, 2011 - Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today announced the appointment of Jaishankar (Jai) Adhinarayanan as VP, Global Service Management Centers.\r\n\r\nMr. Jaishankar joins Futurestep with an incredible depth of experience in the management of service organizations, with a concentration on start-ups and process improvement of HRO, BPO and ITES operations. Most recently, he was the General Manager (Operations/Finance) of Risesmart in India, where he was heading service delivery for the India Center.\r\nPrevious roles include Transformation Leader and Delivery Project Executive at IBM, driving transition, delivery and process redesign within their HRO Operations using lean six sigma practices, and he has also worked in related roles for Exult and ACS. Mr. Jaishankar has spent time working in EMEA, the U.S. and Asia and is a Certified Six Sigma Master Black Belt.\r\n\r\n“Our Service Management Centers (SMCs) around the world are a critical and valued part of the Futurestep infrastructure. The capabilities and expertise centered in our SMCs allow us to provide sophisticated and efficient recruitment solutions that deliver real impact to our clients around the world. Today, we have six global SMCs; in Houston, Shanghai, Bangalore, Warsaw, Auckland, and Sydney and are intending to open a seventh in 2012 in Buenos Aires. Jai’s appointment and deep expertise will undoubtedly further enhance the breadth and quality of services provided by our SMCs. I am delighted he has chosen to join the Futurestep team,” said Futurestep’s Chief Executive Officer Byrne Mulrooney.\r\n\r\nMr. Jaishankar said, “It gives me great pleasure to be a part of the Futurestep family. This is a great opportunity to bring together cutting-edge technology and standardized global operations with the expertise of the Futurestep team. I am looking forward to further developing our capabilities to provide transformational solutions to our clients.”\r\n\r\nAbout Futurestep\r\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions; offering fully customized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs. Our clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure, proprietary competency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to measure and optimize business impact.\r\nAs a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements; from RPO and project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class capability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify, attract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.futurestep.com">www.futurestep.com</a>.\r\n\r\nAbout Korn/Ferry International\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based in Los Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit <a href="http://www.kornferry.com/">http://www.kornferry.com</a> for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and <a href="http://www.kornferryinstitute.com/">http://www.kornferryinstitute.com</a> for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'FUTURESTEP APPOINTS JAI ADHINARAYANAN TO RUN GLOBAL SERVICE MANAGEMENT CENTERS', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1720-revision-8', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:17:13', '2011-10-17 15:17:13', '', 1720, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(779, 2, '2011-10-06 11:05:07', '2011-10-06 11:05:07', 'The Life Sciences practice at Futurestep covers the following sectors; Pharmaceuticals, Medical Devices, Diagnostics, Biotech, Clinical Research Organisations, Consultancies and Service Providers to the Life Science sectors. Within each of the sectors we offer recruitment solutions across all job functions for our clients, these include;\r\n\r\nRegional &amp; Country Managers\r\n\r\nMedical\r\n\r\nR&amp;D\r\n\r\nOperations\r\n\r\nSales\r\n\r\nMarketing\r\n\r\nFinance\r\n\r\nProcurement\r\n\r\nHR\r\n\r\nOur clients range from large Global Corporates to Mid-Size and SME organisations through to Private equity backed and start-up companies. These organisations seek to find, attract, retain and develop high potential talent in order to maintain or gain competitive advantage.\r\n\r\nWe differentiate ourselves by focusing on understanding our Client needs in terms of both functional and cultural fit. Our Consultants have worked within the Life Sciences Markets for many years as recruitment professionals or within the Life Sciences industry itself. This brings an unparallel experience to our teams. Our researchers are multi-lingual and have deep sector experience combined with utilising the best recruitment tools and methodology available within the industry.\r\n\r\nWe are also one of the world‚Äôs largest recruitment services providers operating in the highly competitive life science industry working with a significant proposition of the world‚Äôs leading brands..', 'Life Sciences', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '371-revision-4', '', '', '2011-10-06 11:05:07', '2011-10-06 11:05:07', '', 371, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(780, 1, '2011-10-17 15:10:15', '2011-10-17 15:10:15', '<p>Our specialist financial services team works with many of the world’&#39;s leading banks, insurers and financial services businesses – delivering talent with impact: recruitment solutions that have tangible impact on their performance and competitiveness.\n</p>\n\n<p>Our experience and research-driven approach allows us to identify the best candidates for every role. The use of proven interview and assessment tools enables us to achieve some of the highest delivery and placement rates in the search industry.</p>\n\n<p>\nOur team includes experts who can provide advice and deliver talent in a range of roles and functions, including:\n<ul>\n<li>Front office</li>\n<li>Sales</li>\n<li>Finance</li>\n<li>Risk</li>\n<li>Legal and compliance</li>\n<li>Operations and technology</li>\n</ul>\n</p>', 'Financial Services', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '367-autosave', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:10:15', '2011-10-17 15:10:15', '', 367, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1721, 5, '2011-10-17 15:08:46', '2011-10-17 15:08:46', 'Ms. Patterson is a Consulting Director with Futurestep and brings a wealth of experience related to the recruitment and staffing industry applicant tracking system implementations, on-boarding implementations, vendor relationship management, project upgrade and conversion focuses and global talent management process adaptations.   \n \nFormerly, Ms. Patterson provided support to multiple clients as an implementation consultant as well as a systems analyst on a variety of ATS implementations for Kenexa, Neogov and Vurv Technologies (Currently Taleo). She’s worked on various systems including Kenexa 2xBrassring, Kenexa 2xRecruit, Kenexa 2xOnboading, Vurv Corporate Edition and Aloha. Work included project management, best practice delivery/information, creation of requirements documentation, assisting with development of software solutions with product management following a scrum methodology, developing and delivering training sessions, software configuration, methodology development/continuous improvement, process documentation and execution.  \n', 'Lori Patterson ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1718-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:08:46', '2011-10-17 15:08:46', '', 1718, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
