(1121, 2, '2011-10-10 16:18:27', '2011-10-10 16:18:27', 'One of today‚Äôs most demanding recruiting challenges is competing for talent in a specialized industry. From manufacturing to IT and professional services, skilled and leadership-level talent are critical for business growth in any industry‚Äîand the world of nuclear power generation is no exception.\r\n\r\nToday, Bruce Power provides 20 percent of Ontario‚Äôs energy, operates the second largest single-site nuclear facility in the world, and is currently expanding its operations to meet tremendous growth in energy demand. The company was established in 2001 when a partnership of Canadian companies took over a government-run operation to form Ontario‚Äôs largest independent power generator. Bruce Power operates six reactors, is refurbishing two additional facilities for completion in 2015, and has applied for new-build permission to expand facilities‚Äîbut effective growth requires great talent.\r\n\r\nTo support planned growth and address talent needs, company leaders began an effort in 2006 to assess and redesign recruiting operations. There were several recruiting challenges. First, the company‚Äôs culture reflected the legacy of its roots as a site-based operation of a much larger organization. The company lacked a clearly articulated model to establish expectations of\r\n\r\nleadership. There was an emphasis on technical skills over leadership capability when selecting new hires. A more focused performance management effort was needed, and, due to its remote location, the company had to draw from a limited talent pool for leadership and highend technical roles.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/FS_BrucePower2.pdf">FS_BrucePower</a>', 'RPO Powers Recruiting for Major Canadian Energy Provider', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rpo-powers-recruiting-for-major-canadian-energy-provider-2', '', '', '2011-10-11 08:30:04', '2011-10-11 08:30:04', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=articles&#038;p=1121', 0, 'articles', '', 0),
(864, 2, '2011-10-10 10:43:51', '2011-10-10 10:43:51', 'Recruitment process outsourcing (RPO) offers the optimal solution to managing challenging resourcing requirements in today‚Äôs volatile economies.\r\n\r\nOperational benefits include process efficiencies and access to expert, flexible, scalable resources. Our clients see significant financial benefits, not just in terms of reduction in cost and time to hire, but through much greater visibility and control of recruitment costs. And working in partnership with our clients we are able to help them realise strategic benefits such as implementing a proactive workforce planning process, reinforcing their employer brand and increasing the quality of talent brought into the business.\r\n\r\nFuturestep has over 13 years experience in developing and building bespoke outsourced recruitment solutions that make a positive commercial impact to our clients. We have an extensive global network, in-depth sector expertise and a wide range of complementary consulting solutions. We employ only the most experienced and innovative recruitment professionals, and as a part of the Korn/Ferry group, incorporate the most sophisticated and developed recruitment tools and expertise into our processes.\r\n\r\n<a title="Financial Services" href="http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/solutions/sector/financial-services">gfhfd</a>', 'Recruitment Process Outsourcing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-54', '', '', '2011-10-10 10:43:51', '2011-10-10 10:43:51', '', 11, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
