(1062, 2, '2011-10-10 15:26:42', '2011-10-10 15:26:42', 'Los Angeles, September, 13, 2011 - Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today announced two significant appointments in its consulting solutions team; Doug Rippey as Global Practice Leader, Workforce Planning, and Dave Marzo as General Manager for Consulting Solutions in North America.\r\n\r\nWith responsibility for the entire global Workforce Planning offering, Mr. Rippey will be tasked with providing best-in-class workforce planning solutions to Futurestep clients across the world.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining the Futurestep business, Mr. Rippey worked at Towers Watson for over ten years, where in 2003 he was one of the initial four consultants to form the Workforce Planning practice.\r\n\r\nFuturestep‚Äôs Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Byrne Mulrooney said about the appointment, ‚ÄúSince joining the Futurestep business late last year, Mr. Rippey has been instrumental in helping Futurestep build and enhance its workforce planning offerings, supporting several strategically important global accounts. His appointment as Global Practice Leader, the first of its kind at Futurestep, is a significant step in the expansion of our global consulting capabilities.\r\n\r\nTaking on the role of General Manager for Consulting in North America, Mr Marzo will be responsible for overall leadership, accountability, and growth of Futurestep''s consulting offerings throughout the United States and Canada.', 'Futurestep Appoints Doug Rippey and Dave Marzo to Consulting Solutions Leadership Roles', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'futurestep-appoints-doug-rippey-and-dave-marzo-to-consulting-solutions-leadership-roles', '', '', '2011-10-10 15:50:41', '2011-10-10 15:50:41', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=news&#038;p=1062', 0, 'news', '', 0),
