(1180, 2, '2011-10-10 18:26:10', '2011-10-10 18:26:10', 'Tanya Bennett is the Global Operations Leader for Recruitment Process Outsourcing for Futurestep. She joined the company‚Äôs North America team in 2002 as the Director of Managed Services.\r\n\r\nPrior¬† to joining Futurestep, Ms. Bennett worked for Corestaff Services as Vice President of Performance Partnerships. Overseeing programs that accounted for approximately $400 million in revenue, her diversified client base included financial services, healthcare, industrial practices, technical and business services.\r\n\r\nMs. Bennett has 20 years of experience in the staffing industry, including onsite and project staffing, as well as extensive operations management. She began her career in 1987 with Talent Tree Personnel as a Staffing Consultant and was later named Regional Services Director.\r\n\r\nMs. Bennett graduated from Ripon College in Wisconsin with a bachelor‚Äôs degree in English and Business Management.', 'Tanya Bennett', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '900-revision-10', '', '', '2011-10-10 18:26:10', '2011-10-10 18:26:10', '', 900, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1181, 2, '2011-10-11 10:20:14', '2011-10-11 10:20:14', 'Byrne Mulrooney is CEO of Futurestep, the global talent solutions provider and Korn/Ferry subsidiary. Since 2010, when he assumed this position, Byrne has grown the company from strength to strength.\r\n\r\nWith over 25 years experience in the professional services and outsourcing markets, Byrne has held executive positions in some of the biggest businesses in the world, including IBM and EDS. Often lauded by colleagues for his visionary strategy, and straight talking approach, Byrne has been responsible for bringing together all aspects of the Futurestep business.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Futurestep, Byrne was partner, President and COO of Flynn Transportation Services, a third party logistics company specializing in movement of high-value, time sensitive freight. Prior to that role, for almost four years he served as president of staffing and workforce solutions at Spherion. In this capacity, he led the company‚Äôs $1.5 billion workforce solutions business in North America, which included recruitment process outsourcing and managed services.\r\n\r\nByrne is a graduate of Villanova University in Pennsylvania, and he holds a master''s degree in management from Northwestern University''s J.L. Kellogg Graduate School of Management.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Byrne Mulrooney', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'byrne-mulrooney', '', '', '2011-10-12 18:30:02', '2011-10-12 18:30:02', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1181', 50, 'experts', '', 0),
(1193, 2, '2011-10-12 18:11:45', '2011-10-12 18:11:45', 'Joel Perrenoud is the President of Futurestep across Europe, Middle East and Africa, and brings over fifteen years of professional experience in a wide range of functions and industries to the Futurestep team.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Joel was the Managing Director of Adecco IT &amp; Engineering in Switzerland, where he successfully turned around and repositioned the business with a clear focus on managed services and long-term contracts. Originally Joel started his career at Adecco as Vice President, Global Business Development, Adecco IT &amp; Engineering.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, Joel was Adecco‚Äôs European thought leader on RPO, having led the full sales ‚Äì implementation ‚Äì operation cycle of a number of RPO contracts. Joel started his career at Adecco as the VP Global Business Development for Adecco IT &amp; Engineering.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Joel was an investment manager at the Jacobs Holding AG, responsible for the active management of a portfolio company and part of the core team responsible for the evaluation and execution of new Private Equity investments. He was also Board member and operational manager of KJJ Transportation, Jacobs Holding AG‚Äôs private jet business. Joel has also worked for analysts, McKinsey in San Francisco as a senior consultant, working on a wide range of industry sectors.\r\n\r\nJoel achieved a Master of Business Administration (MBA) with distinction from Harvard Business School, and a degree in economics from the University of Neuch?¢tel, Switzerland. He is a member of the Harvard Club of Switzerland and the Swiss American Chamber of Commerce.', 'Joel Perrenoud', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1191-autosave', '', '', '2011-10-12 18:11:45', '2011-10-12 18:11:45', '', 1191, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
