(1198, 2, '2011-10-11 10:37:32', '2011-10-11 10:37:32', 'William (Bill) Sebra is President of Futurestep‚ North America business, where he is responsible for the continued growth of Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), consulting and retained search services across the region.\r\n\r\nBill brings to Futurestep a vast array of experience as founder and co-founder of multiple successful businesses over the last twenty five years. Known across the US RPO industry, Bill is highly regarded as a pioneer by his peers.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Futurestep, Bill was General Manager at RiseSmart Corporation, where he created a new RPO service line to complement its outplacement business. Prior to RiseSmart, he was Vice President at The Bartech Group, where he oversaw the strategic development and growth of its RPO division, as well as creation of the company‚Äôs Government Solutions Group.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Bill was President and CEO of Kenexa Government Solutions, formerly Knowledge Workers, Inc., a technology enabled human capital solutions company which he founded and grew to 160 people before it was bought by Kenexa in 2006.\r\n\r\nElsewhere, Bill founded The Wilshire Group, a contingency and executive search firm specializing in the defense and intelligence marketplace. He was also a co-founder of Destech Corporation, a software development company that built automated picture database management systems for the CIA.\r\n\r\nA regular speaker and attendee at industry events, Bill has more than written a number of articles and papers on outsourced recruitment initiatives and recruitment trends.', 'William Sebra', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'william-sebra', '', '', '2011-10-12 18:16:57', '2011-10-12 18:16:57', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1198', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1199, 1, '2011-10-11 10:34:44', '2011-10-11 10:34:44', 'Bruce Power provides 20 percent of Ontario, Canada‚Äôs energy and operates the largest single-site nuclear facility\r\nin the world. The company was established in 2001 when a partnership took over a government-run operation to form\r\nOntario‚Äôs largest independent power generator and Canada‚Äôs first private nuclear company. Bruce Power\r\noperates six reactors and is refurbishing two additional facilities for completion in 2010.\r\n\r\nChallenge\r\nBruce Power is expanding its operations to meet tremendous growth in energy demand. The company\r\nassessed its recruiting operations in preparation for a new approach to talent acquisition, and several challenges were\r\nidentified:\r\n‚Ä¢ The company‚Äôs culture reflected the legacy of its roots as a site-based operation of a much larger organization.\r\n‚Ä¢ The company lacked a clearly articulated model to establish expectations of leadership.\r\n‚Ä¢ There was an emphasis on technical skills over leadership capability when selecting new hires.\r\n‚Ä¢ Due to its remote location, Bruce Power had to draw from a limited talent pool for leadership and high-end\r\ntechnical roles.\r\n\r\nApproach\r\nBruce Power developed a comprehensive human capital management framework, focusing on a desired talent ‚Äúend\r\nstate‚Äù and reflecting a long-term view of talent operations. A broad strategic vision was required, addressing all\r\naspects of recruiting and talent management. The Futurestep-Bruce Power approach features performance\r\nmanagement and leadership development expertise from Korn/Ferry and Strategic RPO solutions from Futurestep.\r\nActivity in this relationship includes:\r\n‚Ä¢ Extensive strategic planning to define leadership needs and critical competencies\r\n‚Ä¢ Assessment of current leadership capabilities and gap analysis.\r\n‚Ä¢ Succession and replacement planning\r\n‚Ä¢ Application of behavioral competencies to define needs, identify fit, and facilitate leadership development.\r\n\r\nResults\r\n‚Ä¢ Bruce Power is prepared to foster the leadership it needs to support growing services over the next decade.\r\n‚Ä¢ The company achieved targeted recruitment for key midlevel management roles and critical VP positions.\r\n‚Ä¢ New talent features a blend of nuclear trained employees as well as top performers from outside the industry.\r\n‚Ä¢ A vast majority of recent hires are exceeding performance expectations.\r\n‚Ä¢ A succession planning system is in place to identify, develop and manage talent to enrich Bruce Power‚Äôs talent pipeline.', 'Bruce Power', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1137-revision-6', '', '', '2011-10-11 10:34:44', '2011-10-11 10:34:44', '', 1137, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
