(1221, 1, '2011-10-11 13:41:30', '2011-10-11 13:41:30', 'Catholic Health Initiatives (CHI) is a national nonprofit health organization based in the U.S. The system includes 72 hospitals; 42 long-term care, assisted- and residential living facilities; and two community health-services organizations in 19 states.\r\n<h2>Challenge</h2>\r\nCHI needed a solution to fill a variety of long-standing positions and address new hiring needs as they arose. To achieve a competitive recruiting capability, Futurestep worked with CHI to identify and address fundamental recruiting challenges, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Long-Standing Position Openings - Positions ranged from recent openings to multiple vacancies, including difficult-to-fill medical technology skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Increase Pipeline and Boost Applicant Quality - Traditional job board and Web postings created no access to passive candidates. Interview and selection processes had difficulty keeping up with demand.</li>\r\n	<li>Relieve Overburdened Internal Resources - Recruiters had to handle a large volume of unmanageable candidate traffic. Hiring managers were expected to screen applicants and sift through a large volume of resumes.</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple Strategic Recruiting Issues - Challenges included recruitment metrics and reliance on third-party placement services.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Approach</h2>\r\nThe Futurestep-CHI RPO approach is characterized by a series of progressively strategic efforts delivering successful hiring results and process improvements. Activity in this relationship includes:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pilot Program Serves as the Basis for RPO Relationship - The initial effort was aimed at filling difficult positions. Early tactical success helped establish a foundation for further evolution of internal processes.</li>\r\n	<li>Realignment of Recruiter and Hiring Manager Roles - Futurestep worked with a CHI HR generalist recruiter resource to shift responsibility to a team of dedicated recruiters. As a result, hiring managers received an improved quality of candidates for review and eliminated what was previously an overwhelming screening burden.</li>\r\n	<li>Strategic Improvement‚ÄîBased on early success in filling difficult positions, Futurestep worked with CHI to address strategic challenges, including recruitment brand and compensation strategy. The result was a further improvement in hiring efficiency, candidate acceptance and retention.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>90% Retention Rate for Placements</li>\r\n	<li>40% Decrease in Cycle Time</li>\r\n	<li>50% Reduction in Cost-Per-Hire</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Catholic Health Initiatives', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'catholic-health-initiatives', '', '', '2011-10-12 18:11:34', '2011-10-12 18:11:34', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=case-studies&#038;p=1221', 0, 'case-studies', '', 0),
(1222, 1, '2011-10-11 14:29:12', '2011-10-11 14:29:12', 'Founded in 1945, Kaiser Permanente is the nation‚Äôs largest not-forprofit health plan, serving 8.7 million members. With headquarters in Oakland, California and 160,000 employees across the country, the company is a leader in healthcare and noted for its pioneering role in pre-paid insurance, physicians group practices, prevention and organized service delivery.\r\n<h2>Challenges</h2>\r\nIn 2006, the company began looking at ways to increase operational performance of its highly decentralized recruitment function. Driven by a need to lower vacancy rates, time-to-fill, cost-per-fill, and increase customer satisfaction and quality of hire, Kaiser turned to consultants from The Newman Group, a Futurestep Company, for strategic partnership and support. Key operational challenges included:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lack of a Comprehensive Strategy: No single strategy that could create organizational alignment and target key infrastructure issues that needed to be addressed</li>\r\n	<li>Disparate Processes: A decentralized recruitment organization, including eight separate regions and a corporate recruitment organization</li>\r\n	<li>Separate Systems: Multiple, disparate applicant tracking systems with minimal HRIS integration</li>\r\n	<li>A Variety of Stakeholders: Multiple organizational leaders, each with a significant role in the overall recruitment strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Need to Manage to Metrics: A need to create organizational consistency, clarity and accountability regarding key recruitment metrics</li>\r\n	<li>Need for Enterprise Advantage: A strong push to improve resource allocation for strategic activities that could be consistent across the enterprise</li>\r\n	<li>Improve Candidate, Pipeline and Customer Results: A need to improve brand consistency, achieve a proactive pipeline and increase manager satisfaction</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Approach</h2>\r\nTalent strategy experts from The Newman Group/Futurestep worked with Kaiser to develop a plan that would transform the recruitment function while working within its decentralized structure. The resulting relationship encompassed:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Development of Recruitment Long Term Strategy: The long range strategy and business plan centered around five program areas (customer interaction, management execution, operational excellence, upgrading talent/skills and service delivery)</li>\r\n	<li>Deployment of a Center of Excellence (CoE): The COE centralized recruiting strategic activities that could be standardized across the enterprise</li>\r\n	<li>Business Case/Internal Support: This included business case development and strategic change management to build internal support for transforming the recruitment function</li>\r\n	<li>Single Applicant Tracking System: Management of a vendor selection process for identifying the talent solution best suited to the company‚Äôs unique needs and support a multi-phased implementation based on region deployment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Key recruitment metrics saw vacancy rates decline by 60%, time to fill drop by 25% and customer satisfaction increase by over 20%</li>\r\n	<li>On-time/on-budget system implementation with phased deployment across regional organizations</li>\r\n	<li>Scalable service delivery model to facilitate talent management strategy throughout the enterprise</li>\r\n	<li>Proactive candidate pipeline development now possible with cross enterprise processes</li>\r\n	<li>Consistent process and candidate service now ensures an improved recruitment capability and supports a quality employment brand experience</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Kaiser Permanente', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kaiser-permanente-2', '', '', '2011-10-12 18:13:24', '2011-10-12 18:13:24', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=case-studies&#038;p=1222', 0, 'case-studies', '', 0),
