itment function while working within its decentralized structure. The resulting relationship encompassed:\r\n‚Ä¢ Development of Recruitment Long Term Strategy: The long range strategy and business plan centered around five program areas (customer interaction, management execution, operational excellence, upgrading talent/skills and service delivery)\r\n‚Ä¢ Deployment of a Center of Excellence (CoE): The COE centralized recruiting strategic activities that could be standardized across the enterprise\r\n‚Ä¢ Business Case/Internal Support: This included business case development and strategic change management to build internal support for transforming the recruitment function\r\n‚Ä¢ Single Applicant Tracking System: Management of a vendor selection process for identifying the talent solution best suited to the company‚Äôs unique needs and support a multi-phased implementation based on region deployment\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n‚Ä¢ Key recruitment metrics saw vacancy rates decline by 60%, time to fill drop by 25% and customer satisfaction increase by over 20%\r\n‚Ä¢ On-time/on-budget system implementation with phased deployment across regional organizations\r\n‚Ä¢ Scalable service delivery model to facilitate talent management strategy throughout the enterprise\r\n‚Ä¢ Proactive candidate pipeline development now possible with crossenterprise processes\r\n‚Ä¢ Consistent process and candidate service now ensures an improved recruitment capability and supports a quality employment brand experience', 'Kaiser Permanente', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1222-revision-5', '', '', '2011-10-11 14:46:12', '2011-10-11 14:46:12', '', 1222, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1262, 1, '2011-10-11 14:22:57', '2011-10-11 14:22:57', 'Catholic Health Initiatives (CHI) is a national nonprofit health organization based in the U.S. The system includes 72 hospitals; 42 long-term care, assisted- and residential living facilities; and two community health-services organizations in 19 states.\r\n<h2>Challenge</h2>\r\nCHI needed a solution to fill a variety of long-standing positions and address new hiring needs as they arose. To achieve a competitive recruiting capability, Futurestep worked with CHI to identify and address fundamental recruiting challenges, including:\r\n‚Ä¢ Long-Standing Position Openings - Positions ranged from recent openings to multiple vacancies, including difficult-to-fill medical technology skills.\r\n‚Ä¢ Increase Pipeline and Boost Applicant Quality - Traditional job board and Web postings created no access to passive candidates. Interview and selection processes had difficulty keeping up with demand.\r\n‚Ä¢ Relieve Overburdened Internal Resources - Recruiters had to handle a large volume of unmanageable candidate traffic. Hiring managers were expected to screen applicants and sift through a large volume of resumes.\r\n‚Ä¢ Multiple Strategic Recruiting Issues - Challenges included recruitment metrics and reliance on third-party placement services.\r\n<h2>Approach</h2>\r\nThe Futurestep-CHI RPO approach is characterized by a series of progressively strategic efforts delivering successful hiring results and process improvements. Activity in this relationship includes:\r\n‚Ä¢ Pilot Program Serves as the Basis for RPO Relationship - The initial effort was aimed at filling difficult positions. Early tactical success helped establish a foundation for further evolution of internal processes.\r\n‚Ä¢ Realignment of Recruiter and Hiring Manager Roles - Futurestep worked with a CHI HR generalist recruiter resource to shift responsibility to a team of dedicated recruiters. As a result, hiring managers received an improved quality of candidates for review and eliminated what was previously an overwhelming screening burden.\r\n‚Ä¢ Strategic Improvement‚ÄîBased on early success in filling difficult positions, Futurestep worked with CHI to address strategic challenges, including recruitment brand and compensation strategy. The result was a further improvement in hiring efficiency, candidate acceptance and retention.\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n‚Ä¢ 90% Retention Rate for Placements\r\n‚Ä¢ 40% Decrease in Cycle Time\r\n‚Ä¢ 50% Reduction in Cost-Per-Hire', 'Catholic Health Initiatives', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1221-revision-12', '', '', '2011-10-11 14:22:57', '2011-10-11 14:22:57', '', 1221, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1263, 1, '2011-10-11 13:21:49', '2011-10-11 13:21:49', 'Bruce Power provides 20 percent of Ontario, Canada‚Äôs energy and operates the largest single-site nuclear facility in the world. The company was established in 2001 when a partnership took over a government-run operation to form Ontario‚Äôs largest independent power generator and Canada‚Äôs first private nuclear company. Bruce Power operates six reactors and is refurbishing two additional facilities for completion in 2010.\r\n<h2>Challenge</h2>\r\nBruce Power is expanding its operations to meet tremendous growth in energy demand. The company assessed its recruiting operations in preparation for a new approach to talent acquisition, and several challenges were identified:\r\n‚Ä¢ The company‚Äôs culture reflected the legacy of its roots as a site-based operation of a much larger organization.\r\n‚Ä¢ The company lacked a clearly articulated model to establish expectations of leadership.\r\n‚Ä¢ There was an emphasis on technical skills over leadership capability when selecting new hires.\r\n‚Ä¢ Due to its remote location, Bruce Power had to draw from a limited talent pool for leadership and high-end technical roles.\r\n<h2>Approach</h2>\r\nBruce Power developed a comprehensive human capital management framework, focusing on a desired talent ‚Äúend state‚Äù and reflecting a long-term view of talent operations. A broad strategic vision was required, addressing all aspects of recruiting and talent management. The Futurestep-Bruce Power approach features performance management and leadership development expertise from Korn/Ferry and Strategic RPO solutions from Futurestep. Activity in this relationship includes:\r\n‚Ä¢ Extensive strategic planning to define leadership needs and critical competencies\r\n‚Ä¢ Assessment of current leadership capabilities and gap analysis.\r\n‚Ä¢ Succession and replacement planning\r\n‚Ä¢ Application of behavioral competencies to define needs, identify fit, and facilitate leadership development.\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n‚Ä¢ Bruce Power is prepared to foster the leadership it needs to support growing services over the next decade.\r\n‚Ä¢ The company achieved targeted recruitment for key midlevel management roles and critical VP positions.\r\n‚Ä¢ New talent features a blend of nuclear trained employees as well as top performers from outside the industry.\r\n‚Ä¢ A vast majority of recent hires are exceeding performance expectations.\r\n‚Ä¢ A succession planning system is in place to identify, develop and manage talent to enrich Bruce Power‚Äôs talent pipeline.\r\n<h6><a href="http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/FS_BrucePower3.pdf">Download as PDF</a></h6>', 'Bruce Power', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1137-revision-21', '', '', '2011-10-11 13:21:49', '2011-10-11 13:21:49', '', 1137, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1264, 2, '2011-10-11 10:51:56', '2011-10-11 10:51:56', 'The Employment Value Proposition (EVP) is the collection of key attributes that drive brand perception among employees and candidates. The brand can help you attract and retain talent, or it can drive talent to competitors. Recognizing the value of the employment brand, many companies are taking a disciplined approach to defining the EVP. Today, the EVP can be treated as a company asset that can be measured, managed and improved.\r\n\r\nFuturestep can help you take control of your EVP, leveraging proven principles and best practices to understand your audience, align your brand with the needs and values of your audience, and track the impact of your branding efforts as they evolve. With an EVP strategy in place, your organization can realize positive impact across all facets of talent management.', 'Employer Branding', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '282-revision-21', '', '', '2011-10-11 10:51:56', '2011-10-11 10:51:56', '', 282, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
