andidates for review and eliminated what was previously an overwhelming screening burden.\r\n‚Ä¢ Strategic Improvement‚ÄîBased on early success in filling difficult positions, Futurestep worked with CHI to address strategic challenges, including recruitment brand and compensation strategy. The result was a further improvement in hiring efficiency, candidate acceptance and retention.\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n‚Ä¢ 90% Retention Rate for Placements\r\n‚Ä¢ 40% Decrease in Cycle Time\r\n‚Ä¢ 50% Reduction in Cost-Per-Hire', 'Catholic Health Initiatives', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1221-revision-14', '', '', '2011-10-11 15:05:31', '2011-10-11 15:05:31', '', 1221, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1272, 2, '2011-09-29 14:16:50', '2011-09-29 14:16:50', 'HONG KONG, August 18, 2011 ‚Äì Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today announced that it has appointed Chong Ng as Business Development Director for the Asia region. Mr. Ng has been appointed to help grow the company‚Äôs RPO (Recruitment Process Outsourcing) business and enhance Futurestep‚Äôs go-to-market strategy across Asia.\r\nBased in Hong Kong, with a focus across Asia, Mr. Ng will work closely with Futurestep and Korn/Ferry‚Äôs APAC leadership team to develop and deliver large‚Äìscale solutions in China, Singapore, Malaysia and Hong Kong.\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Ng was the founder and Managing Director of Vantage Limited where he spent the past three years providing clients with outsourcing and IT consulting advisory services across Asia. Notably, Mr. Ng brings with him a wealth of leadership and outsourcing expertise having led a sales practice across thirteen countries in Asia Pacific as well as having negotiated significant outsourcing contracts in major markets during his 20 years with EDS in Asia and in the US.\r\n‚ÄúChong joins Futurestep at an exciting time and his appointment further reflects the importance of our Asia business" said James Mendes, Managing Director, Futurestep, Asia. ‚ÄúChong brings significant Asia and international outsourcing experience to Futurestep. He will play an integral role in developing and advancing our strong RPO presence and reputation in markets across Asia."\r\n‚ÄúAs we look to increase our RPO presence and develop additional capabilities across Asia, Chong‚Äôs wealth of experience coupled with his considerable local market knowledge will be a significant asset to our business,‚Äù continued Mendes. ‚ÄúWe have built real momentum, bringing on board a high calibre team of people with outstanding market knowledge, experience and impact that will enable us to further develop a truly client-focused business.‚Äù\r\n‚ÄúFuturestep‚Äôs existing footprint and track record in Asia provide us with the perfect platform from which to refine our RPO offering in the region to current and new clients,‚Äù said Mr. Ng. Mr. Ng has an MBA (Finance) from Ball State University in Indiana and a BA (History &amp; Religion) from Wabash College in Indiana.\r\nAbout Futurestep\r\nFuturestep is a Korn/Ferry Company and a leading global talent acquisition solutions provider, helping companies build and implement strategies for improving their talent acquisition operations. Key areas of focus include Talent Acquisition Consulting, Recruitment Process Outsourcing, Project-based Recruitment and Mid-Level Recruitment. With operations on four continents, Futurestep provides the experience and expertise to address the most pressing talent acquisition challenges facing companies today. To learn more, visit http://www.futurestep.com.\r\nAbout Korn/Ferry International\r\nNEWS\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based in Los Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit http://www.kornferry.com for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and http://www.kornferryinstitute.com for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'Chong Ng Joins Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry Ccompany, as Business Ddevelopment Direcotor Asia', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '403-revision-6', '', '', '2011-09-29 14:16:50', '2011-09-29 14:16:50', '', 403, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1273, 2, '2011-10-11 11:08:20', '2011-10-11 11:08:20', 'Roberto Spuri is Managing Director of Futurestep in the Latin America region. Responsible for driving growth of Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), consulting and retained search services across the region, Roberto brings to Futurestep a wealth of experience in the HR outsourcing arena.\r\n\r\nRoberto joined the Futurestep in May 2011 from Convergys, which was acquired by NorthgateArinso, where for over four years he led the organization‚Äôs services delivery and client relationship management divisions in Brazil.\r\n\r\nPrior to Convergys, Roberto led strategy deployment for Accenture HR Services‚Äô Latin America region, acting as a solution architect for almost five years. As leader of the company‚Äôs Curitiba/PR HR Shared Service Center, he was in charge of operational design, systems implementation, infrastructure activation, personal hiring, service delivery management and change management programs related to Personal Administration, Benefits and Payroll services. While at Accenture, he also led the deployment and implementation of an insourced HR Shared Service Center for a leading industrial company in Venezuela.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Accenture, Roberto held successful HR roles across multiple industries. As HR Manager at DirecTV do Brasil Ltda., he played a critical part in the implementation of an ERP HR system for Latin America Operations, as well as labor relations activity.¬† At Philip Morris do Brasil, his areas of focus began with compensation and quickly grew to HR management. Prior to Philip Morris, he held compensation and HR management roles at Eurofarma Pharmaceutical Company, and Oxiteno S.A. ‚Äì Chemical/Petrochemical.\r\n\r\nRoberto holds a post graduate business degree from Centro Universit?°rio Municipal de S?£o Caetano do Sul in S?£o Paulo, Brazil.', 'Roberto Spuri', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1201-revision-3', '', '', '2011-10-11 11:08:20', '2011-10-11 11:08:20', '', 1201, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
