(1416, 2, '2011-10-12 08:16:20', '2011-10-12 08:16:20', 'Byrne Mulrooney is CEO of Futurestep, the global talent solutions provider and Korn/Ferry subsidiary. Since 2010, when he assumed this position, Byrne has grown the company from strength to strength.\r\n\r\nWith over 25 years experience in the professional services and outsourcing markets, Byrne has held executive positions in some of the biggest businesses in the world, including IBM and EDS. Often lauded by colleagues for his visionary strategy, and straight talking approach, Byrne has been responsible for bringing together all aspects of the Futurestep business.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Futurestep, Byrne was partner, President and COO of Flynn Transportation Services, a third party logistics company specializing in movement of high-value, time sensitive freight. Prior to that role, for almost four years he served as president of staffing and workforce solutions at Spherion. In this capacity, he led the company‚Äôs $1.5 billion workforce solutions business in North America, which included recruitment process outsourcing and managed services.\r\n\r\nByrne is a graduate of Villanova University in Pennsylvania, and he holds a master''s degree in management from Northwestern University''s J.L. Kellogg Graduate School of Management.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Byrne Mulrooney', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1181-revision-6', '', '', '2011-10-12 08:16:20', '2011-10-12 08:16:20', '', 1181, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1417, 2, '2011-10-12 16:54:56', '2011-10-12 16:54:56', 'Tim Nelson is President of Futurestep‚Äôs Asia Pacific region. In this role, he is responsible for overseeing the strategy, growth and profitability of Futurestep operations across Australia, China, Hong Kong, India, Japan, Malaysia, New Zealand, Singapore and Taiwan. Tim is also a member of parent company Korn/Ferry International‚Äôs Asia Pacific Management Committee.\r\n\r\nPrior to his current role, Tim served as the start-up Managing Director of Futurestep Australia. Previously, he was a partner at Korn/Ferry International where he served clients in¬†the banking and funds management sectors across Asia.\r\n\r\nEarlier in his career, Tim spent almost a decade in consulting and management with a major Australian human resource consultancy, where he was recognized for his achievements in recruiting finance, investment, general management and technology professionals before moving into significant management and leadership positions within the company. He started his career working in Melbourne, Chicago and Hong Kong in the Change Management practice at Anderson Consulting (now Accenture).\r\n\r\nTim holds a Bachelor of Arts, a Diploma of Education, and a Masters of Business Administration from the Australian Graduate School of Management, University of New South Wales. He has also completed an Executive Leadership Program at Harvard Business School.', 'Tim Nelson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1188-autosave', '', '', '2011-10-12 16:54:56', '2011-10-12 16:54:56', '', 1188, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
