(1479, 2, '2011-10-11 10:31:39', '2011-10-11 10:31:39', 'Joel Perrenoud is the President of Futurestep across Europe, Middle East and Africa, and brings over fifteen years of professional experience in a wide range of functions and industries to the Futurestep team.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Joel was the Managing Director of Adecco IT &amp; Engineering in Switzerland, where he successfully turned around and repositioned the business with a clear focus on managed services and long-term contracts. Originally Joel started his career at Adecco as Vice President, Global Business Development, Adecco IT &amp; Engineering.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, Joel was Adecco‚Äôs European thought leader on RPO, having led the full sales ‚Äì implementation ‚Äì operation cycle of a number of RPO contracts. Joel started his career at Adecco as the VP Global Business Development for Adecco IT &amp; Engineering.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Joel was an investment manager at the Jacobs Holding AG, responsible for the active management of a portfolio company and part of the core team responsible for the evaluation and execution of new Private Equity investments. He was also Board member and operational manager of KJJ Transportation, Jacobs Holding AG‚Äôs private jet business. Joel has also worked for analysts, McKinsey in San Francisco as a senior consultant, working on a wide range of industry sectors.\r\n\r\nJoel achieved a Master of Business Administration (MBA) with distinction from Harvard Business School, and a degree in economics from the University of Neuch?¢tel, Switzerland. He is a member of the Harvard Club of Switzerland and the Swiss American Chamber of Commerce.', 'Joel Perrenoud', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1191-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-11 10:31:39', '2011-10-11 10:31:39', '', 1191, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
