(1481, 1, '2011-10-12 15:00:21', '2011-10-12 15:00:21', 'Founded in 1945, Kaiser Permanente is the nation‚Äôs largest not-forprofit health plan, serving 8.7 million members. With headquarters in Oakland, California and 160,000 employees across the country, the company is a leader in healthcare and noted for its pioneering role in pre-paid insurance, physicians group practices, prevention and organized service delivery.\r\n<h2>Challenges</h2>\r\nIn 2006, the company began looking at ways to increase operational performance of its highly decentralized recruitment function. Driven by a need to lower vacancy rates, time-to-fill, cost-per-fill, and increase customer satisfaction and quality of hire, Kaiser turned to consultants from The Newman Group, a Futurestep Company, for strategic partnership and support. Key operational challenges included:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lack of a Comprehensive Strategy: No single strategy that could create organizational alignment and target key infrastructure issues that needed to be addressed</li>\r\n	<li>Disparate Processes: A decentralized recruitment organization, including eight separate regions and a corporate recruitment organization</li>\r\n	<li>Separate Systems: Multiple, disparate applicant tracking systems with minimal HRIS integration</li>\r\n	<li>A Variety of Stakeholders: Multiple organizational leaders, each with a significant role in the overall recruitment strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Need to Manage to Metrics: A need to create organizational consistency, clarity and accountability regarding key recruitment metrics</li>\r\n	<li>Need for Enterprise Advantage: A strong push to improve resource allocation for strategic activities that could be consistent across the enterprise</li>\r\n	<li>Improve Candidate, Pipeline and Customer Results: A need to improve brand consistency, achieve a proactive pipeline and increase manager satisfaction</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Approach</h2>\r\nTalent strategy experts from The Newman Group/Futurestep worked with Kaiser to develop a plan that would transform the recruitment function while working within its decentralized structure. The resulting relationship encompassed:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Development of Recruitment Long Term Strategy: The long range strategy and business plan centered around five program areas (customer interaction, management execution, operational excellence, upgrading talent/skills and service delivery)</li>\r\n	<li>Deployment of a Center of Excellence (CoE): The COE centralized recruiting strategic activities that could be standardized across the enterprise</li>\r\n	<li>Business Case/Internal Support: This included business case development and strategic change management to build internal support for transforming the recruitment function</li>\r\n	<li>Single Applicant Tracking System: Management of a vendor selection process for identifying the talent solution best suited to the company‚Äôs unique needs and support a multi-phased implementation based on region deployment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Key recruitment metrics saw vacancy rates decline by 60%, time to fill drop by 25% and customer satisfaction increase by over 20%</li>\r\n	<li>On-time/on-budget system implementation with phased deployment across regional organizations</li>\r\n	<li>Scalable service delivery model to facilitate talent management strategy throughout the enterprise</li>\r\n	<li>Proactive candidate pipeline development now possible with cross enterprise processes</li>\r\n	<li>Consistent process and candidate service now ensures an improved recruitment capability and supports a quality employment brand experience</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Kaiser Permanente', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1222-revision-13', '', '', '2011-10-12 15:00:21', '2011-10-12 15:00:21', '', 1222, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1482, 2, '2011-10-12 16:45:30', '2011-10-12 16:45:30', 'Roberto Spuri is Managing Director of Futurestep in the Latin America region. Responsible for driving growth of Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), consulting and retained search services across the region, Roberto brings to Futurestep a wealth of experience in the HR outsourcing arena.\r\n\r\nRoberto joined the Futurestep in May 2011 from Convergys, which was acquired by NorthgateArinso, where for over four years he led the organization‚Äôs services delivery and client relationship management divisions in Brazil.\r\n\r\nPrior to Convergys, Roberto led strategy deployment for Accenture HR Services‚Äô Latin America region, acting as a solution architect for almost five years. As leader of the company‚Äôs Curitiba/PR HR Shared Service Center, he was in charge of operational design, systems implementation, infrastructure activation, personal hiring, service delivery management and change management programs related to Personal Administration, Benefits and Payroll services. While at Accenture, he also led the deployment and implementation of an insourced HR Shared Service Center for a leading industrial company in Venezuela.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Accenture, Roberto held successful HR roles across multiple industries. As HR Manager at DirecTV do Brasil Ltda., he played a critical part in the implementation of an ERP HR system for Latin America Operations, as well as labor relations activity.¬† At Philip Morris do Brasil, his areas of focus began with compensation and quickly grew to HR management. Prior to Philip Morris, he held compensation and HR management roles at Eurofarma Pharmaceutical Company, and Oxiteno S.A. ‚Äì Chemical/Petrochemical.\r\n\r\nRoberto holds a post graduate business degree from Centro Universit?°rio Municipal de S?£o Caetano do Sul in S?£o Paulo, Brazil.', 'Roberto Spuri', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1201-revision-16', '', '', '2011-10-12 16:45:30', '2011-10-12 16:45:30', '', 1201, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1483, 2, '2011-10-11 10:33:54', '2011-10-11 10:33:54', 'Masao Sasaki is Futurestep‚Äôs Vice President of Finance, based in Los Angeles. Masao is responsible for all accounting and finance activities for Futurestep, including global and regional financial reporting, financial planning, global SOX compliance, and overseeing Futurestep‚Äôs internal accounting processes and controls.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep in 2006, Masao spent eight years in the private accounting sector, working in Controller-level positions for Simpson Housing Solutions, LLC, an affordable housing developer, and Guidance Solutions, a privately held consulting firm. Earlier in his career, he spent six years in public accounting, beginning his career at Deloitte.\r\n\r\nMasao earned his bachelor‚Äôs degree in Business Economics, with a concentration in Accounting, from the University of California, Santa Barbara.', 'Masao Sasaki', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1195-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-11 10:33:54', '2011-10-11 10:33:54', '', 1195, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
