(1485, 2, '2011-10-12 16:54:08', '2011-10-12 16:54:08', 'Tim Nelson is President of Futurestep‚Äôs Asia Pacific region. In this role, he is responsible for overseeing the strategy, growth and profitability of Futurestep operations across Australia, China, Hong Kong, India, Japan, Malaysia, New Zealand, Singapore and Taiwan. Tim is also a member of parent company Korn/Ferry International‚Äôs Asia Pacific Management Committee.\r\n\r\nPrior to his current role, Tim served as the start-up Managing Director of Futurestep Australia. Previously, he was a partner at Korn/Ferry International where he served clients in¬†the banking and funds management sectors across Asia.\r\n\r\nEarlier in his career, Tim spent almost a decade in consulting and management with a major Australian human resource consultancy, where he was recognized for his achievements in recruiting finance, investment, general management and technology professionals before moving into significant management and leadership positions within the company. He started his career working in Melbourne, Chicago and Hong Kong in the Change Management practice at Anderson Consulting (now Accenture).\r\n\r\nTim holds a Bachelor of Arts, a Diploma of Education, and a Masters of Business Administration from the Australian Graduate School of Management, University of New South Wales. He has also completed an Executive Leadership Program at Harvard Business School.', 'Tim Nelson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1188-revision-5', '', '', '2011-10-12 16:54:08', '2011-10-12 16:54:08', '', 1188, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1486, 2, '2011-10-12 16:44:00', '2011-10-12 16:44:00', 'Sean Kent is Global Technology Leader for Futurestep, responsible for the company‚Äôs strategic development, acquisition and use of business technology solutions worldwide.\r\n\r\nThis role includes the application of talent management technology for internal and external service delivery, business intelligence, analytics, and reporting initiatives, as well as management of technology supplier relationships.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, Sean serves as the Futurestep liaison to Korn/Ferry‚Äôs global IT team, working closely to leverage and accelerate the full capabilities of the company‚Äôs global technology platforms across the organization.\r\n\r\nSean joined Futurestep as part of The Newman Group, which was acquired by Futurestep in 2007. As a consulting director, he led strategic talent management technology initiatives for a diverse portfolio of Fortune 500 clients. Prior to joining The Newman Group, Sean managed recruiting technology and operations nationally for DeVry Inc.¬† Elsewhere, he has previously held leadership roles in the executive search industry with national firms including Technisource, a Spherion Company.\r\n\r\nSean serves on the Board of Directors of Atlanta chapter of the International Association for Human Resources Information Management (IHRIM), and he has presented at several industry conferences and professional association meetings for organizations including IHRIM and the Electronic Recruiting Exchange (ERE).\r\n\r\nSean holds a bachelor‚Äôs degree in English from the University of Florida, and an MBA in Human Resources Management from Keller Graduate School.', 'Sean Kent', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '897-revision-9', '', '', '2011-10-12 16:44:00', '2011-10-12 16:44:00', '', 897, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
