(1495, 2, '2011-10-12 17:52:00', '2011-10-12 17:52:00', 'William (Bill) Sebra is President of Futurestep‚ North America business, where he is responsible for the continued growth of Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), consulting and retained search services across the region.\r\n\r\nBill brings to Futurestep a vast array of experience as founder and co-founder of multiple successful businesses over the last twenty five years. Known across the US RPO industry, Bill is highly regarded as a pioneer by his peers.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Futurestep, Bill was General Manager at RiseSmart Corporation, where he created a new RPO service line to complement its outplacement business. Prior to RiseSmart, he was Vice President at The Bartech Group, where he oversaw the strategic development and growth of its RPO division, as well as creation of the company‚Äôs Government Solutions Group.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Bill was President and CEO of Kenexa Government Solutions, formerly Knowledge Workers, Inc., a technology enabled human capital solutions company which he founded and grew to 160 people before it was bought by Kenexa in 2006.\r\n\r\nElsewhere, Bill founded The Wilshire Group, a contingency and executive search firm specializing in the defense and intelligence marketplace. He was also a co-founder of Destech Corporation, a software development company that built automated picture database management systems for the CIA.\r\n\r\nA regular speaker and attendee at industry events, Bill has more than written a number of articles and papers on outsourced recruitment initiatives and recruitment trends.', 'William Sebra', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1198-revision-5', '', '', '2011-10-12 17:52:00', '2011-10-12 17:52:00', '', 1198, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
