(1571, 4, '2011-10-14 12:28:08', '2011-10-14 12:28:08', 'Futurestep are hosting a round table lunch in a series of events aimed at senior HR/talent leaders which cover a wide range of topics and stimulating debate within the talent community.\r\n\r\nThis lunch takes place on 24th November and hosted by Mark Lee, Managing Director of the Futurestep EMEA RPO business, and he will lead the discussion “online talent communities – you have to give to get back!”. Traditionally, talent pools which have been around for years give the impression of a formed and interactive structure when in reality, the focus has been on finding potential candidates from a database list. Mark will reveal how talent communities are evolving and how candidate-driven markets for niche talent demand a different approach. Mark will give an insight in to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How networking technology enables the creation of talent communities to attract new talent</li>\r\n	<li>How to maintain the visibility and impact of organisations to give potential candidates reasons to engage over and above the promise of a job in the future</li>\r\n	<li>Challenges and key wins in delivering the solutions using case study examples Vodafone, Siemens, Microsoft, Roche, Invensys and others</li>\r\n	<li>How to measure return on investment</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Brussels - Round table lunch', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'brussels-round-table-lunch', '', '', '2011-10-14 12:29:10', '2011-10-14 12:29:10', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=news-events&#038;p=1571', 0, 'news-events', '', 0),
