(1592, 5, '2011-10-17 08:46:57', '2011-10-17 08:46:57', 'Tanya Bennett is the Global Operations Leader for Recruitment Process Outsourcing for Futurestep. She joined the company''s North America team in 2002 as the Director of Managed Services.\n\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Bennett worked for Corestaff Services as Vice President of Performance Partnerships. Overseeing programs that accounted for approximately $400 million in revenue, her diversified client base included financial services, healthcare, industrial practices, technical and business services.\n\nMs. Bennett has 20 years of experience in the staffing industry, including onsite and project staffing, as well as extensive operations management. She began her career in 1987 with Talent Tree Personnel as a Staffing Consultant and was later named Regional Services Director.\n\nMs. Bennett graduated from Ripon College in Wisconsin with a bachelor’s degree in English and Business Management.\n', 'Tanya Bennett', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1555-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 08:46:57', '2011-10-17 08:46:57', '', 1555, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1594, 5, '2011-10-17 08:53:28', '2011-10-17 08:53:28', 'Mrs. Brittain has over fifteen years in the recruiting industry. She brings extensive knowledge in the recruiting industry from managing RPOs and  building client relationships. She has executed and managed many different solutions in her career, including Compaq Computers, Continental Airlines, Kellogg, Hershey''s, Hexion Chemicals and Dell.\n\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mrs. Brittain spent eleven years with Recruitment Enhancement Services an Omnicom Group Inc. company, as a Director, Client Services in its recruitment process outsourcing  division.\n\nMrs. Brittain has experience in the areas of recruitment strategy, workflow process, client relationship, technology implementation, vendor relations, metric reports and best practices for achieving an organizations strategic vision and goals.\n \nAdditionally, Mrs. Brittain has worked in various industries such as Consumer Packaged Goods, Specialty Chemicals, Manufacturing, Financial Services, Petroleum, Defense, Government, Information Technology, Engineering Construction,  and Advertising/Marketing.\n \nMrs. Brittain graduated from Texas A&M in 1991 with a Bachelors degree.', 'Dena Brittain', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1593-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 08:53:28', '2011-10-17 08:53:28', '', 1593, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1595, 5, '2011-10-17 09:03:32', '2011-10-17 09:03:32', 'Ms. Cade joined Futurestep in 2002 as a Recruiter quickly advancing to a Senior Recruiter and has served in a management role since 2004. \r\n\r\nCurrently, a Project Director in our Projects division, Ms. Cade is responsible for the deployment of recruitment management solutions, specializing in the Consumer and Industrial practices. She works with global and national clients utilizing best practices and the latest recruitment process efficiencies in each project she manages. \r\n\r\nFurther, Ms. Cade has managed global projects, client relationships and teams of centralized and decentralized Recruiters and Administrative staff.  \r\n\r\nMs. Cade has provided exceptional service delivery for Futurestep clients to include: Halliburton, General Mills, Kraft, Hilton, Rio Tinto, Yum Restaurants International, Goodyear Tire and Rubber, Palm, Morgan Stanley Smith Barney, Response Genetics and Wal-Mart.\r\n\r\nPrior to Joining Futurestep, Ms. Cade was a Senior Consultant with a boutique executive search firm focusing on the recruitment and placement of Executive and Mid-Management talent in the consumer, financial services, manufacturing, publishing and telecommunication industries. Ms. Cade excels at understanding client expectations, motivating her team to perform beyond those expectations, consulting with the client throughout the project and managing through continuous improvement. \r\n\r\nMs. Cade holds a Bachelor of Arts in Political Science from Western Illinois University in Macomb, Illinois.\r\n', 'Germayne Cade', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'germayne-cade', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:44:08', '2011-10-17 16:44:08', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1595', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
