(1597, 5, '2011-10-17 09:09:24', '2011-10-17 09:09:24', 'Ms. Callaway joined Futurestep in 2011 as a Managing Consultant in the Dallas office. With over fifteen years of talent acquisition know-how, Ms. Callaway has served as a strategic partner to cliental ranging from start-ups to Fortune 100 corporations.  \r\n\r\nWorking in multiple verticals including Retail/Consumer, Technology, Industrial, Healthcare Services, Finance, and Consulting, Ms. Callaway is well versed in Corporate Infrastructure as well as Supply Chain and Logistics, but has particular expertise and passion around the Information Technology sector.  \r\n\r\nPrior to joining the firm, Ms. Callaway led the corporate recruiting team for a major retailer through multiple Information Technology transformations. Her corporate experience gives her unique perspective on how to aid corporations in attracting and retaining top talent.   \r\n\r\nEarlier, Ms. Callaway was founder and co-executive of a successful boutique search firm with a niche in technology consulting.  In this role she formed strategic alliances with her client organizations to successfully implement technical projects.  She has served as a consultant to numerous organizations on full life cycle recruiting including strategy architecture, process development, souring, selection, on-boarding, and retention.   \r\n\r\nMs. Callaway has served as an advisor to the CEO of Career Communications in their efforts to promote diversity in the work place and is a member of the National Association of Personnel Staffing and Women Business Enterprise National Council.\r\n', 'Dawn Callaway', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dawn-callaway', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:53:12', '2011-10-17 16:53:12', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1597', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
