(1607, 5, '2011-10-17 09:30:38', '2011-10-17 09:30:38', 'Mr. Candland is client development manager for Futurestep with a focus on the Northeastern America. An expert at delivering RPO solutions to meet highly demanding client needs, he has extensive experience in culture and process customization and innovative candidate quality sourcing using advanced techniques and technologies. \r\n \r\nWith deep recruitment solutions experience in the financial services industry, Mr. Candland has been an executive sponsor and leader of RPO and managed staffing engagements for U.S. and international clients such as Deutsche Bank, UBS, Goldman Sachs, CitiGroup, American Express, Lehman Brothers, Bear Stearns, Standard Chartered Bank and Bridgewater.  \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Candland led the Managed Services Programs business of a US-focused specialty staffing solutions provider based in New York. Prior to that, he co-founded Advantage Human Resourcing and Advantage Global, both leading firms in staffing, contingent workforce management, executive search, RPO and MSP.  \r\n\r\nMr. Candland started his career as a securities market professional and investment banker in capital markets working for NASDAQ, Merrill Lynch and Dean Witter (Morgan Stanley). He earned an MBA from New York University and a BA from the University of Utah.  ', 'Steve Candland', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'steve-candland', '', '', '2011-10-17 17:07:18', '2011-10-17 17:07:18', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1607', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
