(1609, 5, '2011-10-17 09:34:34', '2011-10-17 09:34:34', 'As Director, Service Delivery, Western Canada, Ms. Duncan has overall accountability for the development of strategic client partnerships for single search and project work in Western Canada. \r\n\r\nShe also has responsibility for the allocation and management of\r\nresources, ensuring the quality and timely delivery of Futurestep’s recruitment offerings.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Ms. Duncan was a senior recruiter here at Futurestep and has worked with organizations such as ICBC, BC Hydro, BCAA, Intrawest, Walter Energy, SIAST and The Capital Power Corporation.\r\n\r\nMs. Duncan has spent the past fourteen years working in international recruitment and talent management consulting. Prior to joining Futurestep she managed the Downtown Vancouver branch of an international recruitment firm leading a team responsible for\r\ntemporary, permanent and project recruitment offerings.\r\n\r\nPrior to coming to Canada, Ms. Duncan established the first regional IT organization, outside of London, for Badenoch and Clark, a leading UK recruitment firm, she also managed their finance division in the North West of England.\r\n\r\nMs. Duncan has extensive experience in operational and corporate recruitment in a variety of industries and has assisted her clients to develop strategic talent acquisition plans.\r\n\r\nMs. Duncan holds a Bachelor of Arts degree with honors from the University of Reading (UK), majoring in Politics and International Relations.', 'Samantha Duncan', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'samantha-duncan', '', '', '2011-10-17 17:11:42', '2011-10-17 17:11:42', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1609', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
