(1617, 5, '2011-10-17 09:50:10', '2011-10-17 09:50:10', 'Ms.Grillo is a Senior Recruiter, and part of the US Service Delivery RPO team.  In this capacity, Ms.Grillo is responsible for the execution of end-to-end recruitment services globally and nationwide. \n\nCurrently a member of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission RPO team, Ms.Grillo has successfully completed a recruiting project with the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Functionally, Ms.Grillo has executed searches in HR, Sales and Marketing, Government, Legal, Operations Finance, Accounting, HealthCare and Life Sciences.\n\nMs.Grillo excels at providing exceptional service to her clients including being a proactive consultant, delivering quality talent and superior candidate care.  Her ability to create innovative sourcing strategies to attract passive candidates is sought out by internal and external customers.   \n\nPrior to joining Futurestep in 2010, Ms.Grillo was a Recruiting Manager for the Healthcare Practice with Navigant Consulting for three years. During her tenure, she was responsible for the corporate recruitment process of multiple divisions of the HealthCare and Life Sciences practices and Diversity ERG initiatives. Ms.Grillo also spent over ten years working for organizations such as Yahoo! HotJobs, MicroStrategy, KaBoom!, and Elizabeth Glaser Pediatric AIDS foundation as a Talent Management and Recruitment solutions professional.\n\nMs.Grillo holds a Bachelor of Arts from Howard University. \n', 'Michelle Grillo', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1616-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:50:10', '2011-10-17 09:50:10', '', 1616, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1618, 5, '2011-10-17 09:52:54', '2011-10-17 09:52:54', 'Ms.Hanifen is a Managing Consultant for Futurestep’s US Search Practice and is based in Dallas, TX. Ms.Hanifen brings over twenty years of professional recruitment experience including Agency, Executive Search, and RPO businesses.  \r\n\r\nDuring her tenure with Futurestep, Ms.Hanifen has successfully executed search engagements across a wide range of verticals including Industrial, High Technology, Renewable Energy and Consumer Products.  \r\n\r\nWorking with an array of functions including Sales and Marketing, Engineering, Product Development, Environmental Health and Safety, Quality Assurance, Strategic Sourcing, Procurement,  Supplier Quality, Operations and Corporate Sustainability, Ms.Hanifen has developed an excellent reputation for client satisfaction and high quality candidate care. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep in 2008, Ms.Hanifen served as a Senior Recruiter at Recruitment Enhancement Services (RES), and Texas Instruments where she was responsible for full life cycle recruitment of senior level technical, business development, marketing, product development, scientific and operations personnel.  \r\n\r\nMs.Hanifen holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Liberal Arts and Sciences from DePaul University in Chicago, IL.', 'Cindy Hanifen', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cindy-hanifen', '', '', '2011-10-17 17:22:11', '2011-10-17 17:22:11', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1618', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
