(1632, 5, '2011-10-17 10:32:17', '2011-10-17 10:32:17', 'Ms. MacDonald is the General Manager, RPO and Recruitment Solutions, U.S. for Futurestep and is also a member of Korn/Ferry’s Global Technology Leadership team. She is based in the firm’s Los Angeles office.\r\n\r\nAt Futurestep, Ms. MacDonald is responsible for leading the strategic direction, service delivery and growth of Futurestep’s RPO and Recruitment Projects business in the United States. \r\n\r\nPrior to her current role with Futurestep, Ms. MacDonald was Vice President, Strategic Account Management, responsible for the growth of key client relationships in the U.S. \r\n\r\nJoining the firm in 1998, she has extensive experience working with clients in a variety of industries, including consumer package goods, financial services, life sciences, advanced technology and media convergence.\r\n\r\nMs. MacDonald  began her career  in 1990 as a Client OnSite Manager with Fritz Companies, a Global Logistics provider since acquired by UPS Supply Chain Solutions. She then worked for American Telephone & Telegraph (AT&T) and became the company’s first Internet Marketing Manager based in Silicon Valley and later, a Sales Director in Southern California responsible for voice, data and Web-related services. Ms. MacDonald was recognized by AT&T with a “Gold Club” status, an honor awarded to the top two percent of the organization’s employees for exceeding client expectations.\r\n\r\nMs. MacDonald has served on Korn/Ferry’s Global Partnership Council representing Futurestep, reporting to Korn/Ferry’s CEO. The Council is designed to provide open and honest feedback from senior partners in  Korn/Ferry’s global business, as well as support the Firm’s strategies and initiatives. \r\n\r\nShe holds a bachelor’s degree in both International Relations and French from the University of Virginia.', 'Jeanne MacDonald ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jeanne-macdonald', '', '', '2011-10-17 10:32:17', '2011-10-17 10:32:17', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1632', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
