(1640, 5, '2011-10-17 11:05:51', '2011-10-17 11:05:51', 'Ms. Sidlar joined Futurestep in 2005 as a Managing Consultant for the firm’s Michigan office. Now as the US Director of Client Development, she leads the RPO and Project Recruitment client development team and manages a client base in the Midwest. She brings more than twenty years of experience in the staffing and human capital industries to her role at Futurestep.\r\n\r\nMs. Sidlar and her team provide strategic talent acquisition solutions for key clients based on each company’s unique talent issues. Her Futurestep client base spans multiple industries, with the heaviest focus on consumer products/retail and industrial/manufacturing clients. Key clients include; Belk Department Stores, Boise Paper, Dow Corning, General Mills, Kaiser Permanente, Novartis, Walmart and Zimmer. \r\n\r\nNotably, Ms. Sidlar is an active member of Korn/Ferry’s Global Consumer/Retail Center of Excellence.\r\n \r\nWith an unending attention to detail and focused approach to uncovering the nuances of each engagement, Ms. Sidlar is an exceptional partner to her clients and her team.  Her experience across all of Futurestep’s operating divisions (Search, RPO and Consulting) enables her clients to benefit from the broad range of services available to them.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Sidlar spent eight years at Kelly Services, Inc.  During her last three years there, she served as a Strategic Sales Manager, responsible for driving sales for two corporate-based human resource outsourcing (HRO) divisions, RPO and vendor management.\r\n\r\nMs. Sidlar graduated cum laude with a Bachelor of Arts from Hope College in Holland, MI with degrees in both Communications and Spanish. Additionally, she also completed a foreign study program in Mexico at the Centro Mexicano de Idiomas. Ms. Sidlar is a spokesperson and volunteer for the American Heart Association.\r\n', 'Kristy Sidlar', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kristy-sidlar', '', '', '2011-10-17 11:05:51', '2011-10-17 11:05:51', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1640', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
