(1642, 5, '2011-10-17 11:26:57', '2011-10-17 11:26:57', 'Ms. Weiss is a Managing Consultant for Futurestep’s US Search Practice. Her work spans across a wide range of verticals, including Non Profit, Higher Education, Manufacturing/ Industrial, and Consumer/Retail where she has successfully placed high impact executives across an array of functions, including, Human Resources, Marketing, Finance, and Operational and Management roles.  \r\n\r\nNotably, Ms. Weiss was the 2008 recipient of Futurestep’s North America Chief Executive ''Top Quality'' prize, recognising her efforts over the previous twelve months.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining the search industry, Ms. Weiss had a twelve-year tenure in the New York City publishing world, during which time she held titles such as Editorial Director, Director of Business Development & Planning, as well as Director of Operations at The Princeton Review’s K-12 Services division. Ms. Weiss also served as a Managing Editor at Golden Books for their Education Division/Custom Publishing and was a Production Manager at McGraw Hill K-12 Services Group.  \r\n\r\nMs. Weiss holds Bachelor and Master of Arts degrees in English Literature, as well as a Master of Fine Arts degree in Creative Writing from Brooklyn College. She is an adjunct professor of English and writing at various New York City and Florida universities, and is the author of academic books for Random House, one of which is a career-based book for young adults, 145 Things To Be When You Grow Up. ', 'Jodi Weiss', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jodi-weiss', '', '', '2011-10-17 11:36:37', '2011-10-17 11:36:37', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1642', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
