(1649, 5, '2011-10-17 11:42:32', '2011-10-17 11:42:32', 'Ms. Wong is the Vice President and General Manager of Operations for Futurestep in Canada.  Based in Montreal, she is responsible for overseeing service delivery and operations to ensure the optimization of productivity and quality metrics, including client and candidate satisfaction. Ms. Wong is also responsible for competency and career development and internal mobility.\r\n \r\nPrior to her current role, Ms. Wong was the Service Delivery Leader for Eastern Canada for Futurestep, with diverse responsibilities including recruitment, project management and service delivery excellence.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Futurestep in 2006, Ms. Wong spent over a decade working abroad in Hong Kong and New York City, initially as an Audit Manager with Price Waterhouse Hong Kong.  She then joined Michael Page Hong Kong, where she built and ran its largest division in financial services and helped them achieve recognition as the top recruitment consultancy in Asia within two years of its start up. Ms. Wong subsequently transferred to their New York office and established a highly successful front office banking practice.\r\n\r\nMs. Wong holds a Graduate Diploma in Public Accountancy and a Bachelor’s Degree in Commerce from McGill University. She is a Chartered Accountant. \r\n\r\n', 'Karen Wong', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'karen-wong', '', '', '2011-10-17 11:42:32', '2011-10-17 11:42:32', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1649', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
