(1667, 5, '2011-10-17 13:54:19', '2011-10-17 13:54:19', 'Mr. Rippey is the Global Practice Leader, Workforce Planning for Futurestep''s consulting division.  In this role Mr. Rippey leads the workforce planning practice, driving the strategic direction for the practice through development of global workforce planning offerings, thought leadership and helping to develop tools and toolkits to provide consistent delivery.  \r\n \r\nMr. Rippey is an accomplished talent management consultant with almost 20 years of experience in the space.  He has deep experience in all facets of the workforce planning life cycle, including workforce analytics and metrics, projections of talent needs, business demand planning, external labor market forecasts, talent gap calculations, design of alternative models for cost optimization and HR program recommendations.\r\n \r\nAdditionally, Mr. Rippey has technical and functional knowledge of other areas of talent management, including talent acquisition and onboarding.  He is experienced in leading projects and has a significant track record in working with clients throughout projects – from the sales cycle through final delivery.\r\n\r\nMr. Rippey holds a BBA in Accounting from James Madison University.\r\n', 'Doug Rippey', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'doug-rippey', '', '', '2011-10-17 13:54:19', '2011-10-17 13:54:19', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1667', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
