(1671, 5, '2011-10-17 14:18:49', '2011-10-17 14:18:49', 'Ms. Campopiano is a Principal Consultant with Futurestep, and has over 15 years of Human Resources and Talent Management experience with market-leading global organizations within IT Research and Consulting industries.  She has a specific focus on project management, planning, analysis and execution of integrated Talent Management solutions to enable organizations to maximize their return on people processes. \r\n\r\nPrior to Futurestep Consulting, Ms. Campopiano was a Sr. Manager of HR Process and HR Information Systems at Gartner, Inc.  In this role, she was the change management lead for HR operations, process improvement reviews and for global HRIS system deployment.  Additionally she served as the process leader for re-engineering global recruitment and on-boarding activities. Ms. Campopiano effectively managed the administration of several HR technology applications and related vendors, including SuccessFactors, Kenexa, PeopleAnswers, and Oracle. Prior to Gartner, Inc., Ms. Campopiano served as a workforce planning lead and HR manager at Accenture for the Northeast and Canadian region''s Communications, High-Tech and Media client group.\r\n\r\nMs. Campopiano actively volunteers with a variety of business and career development initiatives. She is the Strategic HR Advisor member of the Supervisory Committee to the Board of Directors for the United Shoreline Federal Credit Union, a professional networking leader for Whine and Dine Human Resources Networking Group and a mentor for college seniors and graduate level students through College2Corporate Marketplace, facilitated at Fairfield University. She is member of the Society for Human Resources Management (SHRM) National and Southern CT Chapters. \r\n\r\nMs. Campopiano holds a Master of Arts in Industrial/Organizational Psychology from Fairfield University and a Bachelor of Liberal Arts in Psychology from the University of Connecticut. \r\n\r\n', 'Elaina Campopiano ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'elaina-campopiano', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:18:49', '2011-10-17 14:18:49', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1671', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1672, 1, '2011-10-17 14:16:18', '2011-10-17 14:16:18', '<p>Working with Futurestep – and effectively with Korn/Ferry means being part of a truly world-class global business. It brings a responsibility to excel but also the opportunity to build a Career with Impact – working with the world&#39;s leading brands and in the company of more than 800 talented and supportive colleagues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are clear about our corporate purpose: we help our clients discover and measure talent with impact to improve performance and gain competitive advantage. Similarly, we&#39;re clear about the kind of talent we need within Futurestep to deliver this premium service to our clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We need people with integrity and a clear moral compass; individuals who are dedicated and determined to learn and grow – independently and within a team context. We value entrepreneurial flair alongside strong analytical and communication skills. Of course, we also recruit colleagues across a range of roles and at all experience levels, but the qualities expressed above are pre-requisites for everyone who joins us. </p>\r\n', 'Working at Futurestep', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'working-at-futurestep', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:09:12', '2011-10-17 16:09:12', '', 506, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?page_id=1672', 2, 'page', '', 0),
(1791, 5, '2011-10-17 16:02:47', '2011-10-17 16:02:47', 'Mr. Moore is a Managing Consultant for Futurestep, responsible for leading senior Accounting and Financial search assignments. With over fourteen years in recruitment, Mr. Moore has extensive experience in Executive Search, RPO and Corporate Recruitment. He has partnered with both Fortune 500 firms and start-ups and is recognized as a trusted advisor in talent acquisition. \n\nPrior to this Mr. Moore worked in Citigroup’s Headquarters and focused on talent acquisition for the Global Transaction Services business.  He joined Citi from a national executive search firm where he was a Managing Partner and ran the Accounting and Finance operation in New York.\n\nEarlier he started the search practice for TMP Worldwide, the parent company of Monster.com, and helped build out the Accounting and Finance division in the Northeast.  TMP spun off and created Hudson Global Resources and Mr. Moore joined their Workforce Solutions team.  He led the RPO engagement with Gartner, Inc. and was responsible for their talent acquisition in the Americas. \n\nMr. Moore graduated from Quinnipiac University in Connecticut with a Bachelor of Science in Business Management and a concentration in Human Resources\n\n\n\n\n', 'Jonathan Moore', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1784-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:02:47', '2011-10-17 16:02:47', '', 1784, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
