(1790, 1, '2011-10-17 16:07:58', '2011-10-17 16:07:58', '<p>As a business that discovers, delivers and maximizes Talent with Impact for many of the world&#39;s most successful businesses – we understand only too well that &#39;personal development&#39; and &#39;career opportunity&#39; are both Top-Five drivers for joining and staying with an employer. We are using this understanding – and our access to state-of-the-art talent management and personal development processes and content via Lominger, a sister Korn/Ferry company – to build a thriving talent community inside our own business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the heart of this initiative is the creation of a unique digital profile or Careerbook for every single Futurestep employee: a personalized ‘&#39;tool’&#39; that enables them to build networks, access best practice and contribute to company-wide initiatives from the first day they join us. But Careerbook is much more than a &#39;tool&#39; – it is also the focus for colleagues&#39; career development throughout their time with us; the means by which they create and actively manage their own skills acquisition and development plan, in partnership with their line manager and with support from our HR team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In simple terms, Careerbook gives every Futurestep colleague more control over the way and the means in which they grow with us. We believe that it represents a fundamental shift – a new &#39;paradigm&#39; – in the way a global business can support and foster colleague development.</p>\r\n', 'Futurestep Careerbook', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'futurestep-careerbook', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:09:21', '2011-10-17 16:09:21', '', 506, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?page_id=1790', 4, 'page', '', 0),
(1674, 5, '2011-10-17 14:11:02', '2011-10-17 14:11:02', 'Ms. Campopiano is a Principal Consultant with Futurestep Consulting, a Korn/Ferry company.  Elaina has over 15 years of Human Resources and Talent Management experience with market-leading global organizations within IT Research and Consulting industries.  She has a specific focus on project management, planning, analysis and execution of integrated Talent Management solutions to enable organizations to maximize their return on people processes. \n\nPrior to Futurestep Consulting, Ms. Campopiano was a Sr. Manager of HR Process and HR Information Systems at Gartner, Inc.  In this role, she was the change management lead for HR operations, process improvement reviews and for global HRIS system deployment.  Additionally she served as the process leader for re-engineering global recruitment and on-boarding activities. Ms. Campopiano effectively managed the administration of several HR technology applications and related vendors, including SuccessFactors, Kenexa, PeopleAnswers, and Oracle. Prior to Gartner, Inc., Ms. Campopiano served as a workforce planning lead and HR manager at Accenture for the Northeast and Canadian region''s Communications, High-Tech and Media client group.\n\nMs. Campopiano actively volunteers with a variety of business and career development initiatives. She is the Strategic HR Advisor member of the Supervisory Committee to the Board of Directors for the United Shoreline Federal Credit Union, a professional networking leader for Whine and Dine Human Resources Networking Group and a mentor for college seniors and graduate level students through College2Corporate Marketplace, facilitated at Fairfield University. She is member of the Society for Human Resources Management (SHRM) National and Southern CT Chapters. \n\nMs. Campopiano holds a Master of Arts in Industrial/Organizational Psychology from Fairfield University and a Bachelor of Liberal Arts in Psychology from the University of Connecticut. \n\n', 'Elaina Campopiano ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1671-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:11:02', '2011-10-17 14:11:02', '', 1671, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1675, 5, '2011-10-17 14:22:22', '2011-10-17 14:22:22', 'Ms. McCarthy is a Managing Consultant with Futurestep. In her role, she is an experienced project manager who provides client services including talent management technology implementation and support. Ms. McCarthy has demonstrated success in strategic high volume and large retail recruitment. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep Consulting, she worked as Human Resources Manager for Lowe’s Home Improvement, held positions of Human Resources Generalist and Regional Recruiter with The Schwan Food Company and worked as a member of the strategic employment team at Baylor Health Care System.\r\n\r\nMs. McCarthy holds a Bachelors degree in Human Resource Management from the Eli Broad College of Business at Michigan State University.  She is a member of the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM) and the Human Capital Institute (HCI) and has achieved her SPHR certification.\r\n', 'Elizabeth McCarthy', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'elizabeth-mccarthy', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:22:22', '2011-10-17 14:22:22', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1675', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1676, 5, '2011-10-17 14:21:16', '2011-10-17 14:21:16', 'Ms. McCarthy is a Managing Consultant with Futurestep. In her role, she is an experienced project manager who provides client services including talent management technology implementation and support. Ms. McCarthy has demonstrated success in strategic high volume and large retail recruitment. \n\nPrior to joining Futurestep Consulting, she worked as Human Resources Manager for Lowe’s Home Improvement, held positions of Human Resources Generalist and Regional Recruiter with The Schwan Food Company and worked as a member of the strategic employment team at Baylor Health Care System.\n\nMs. McCarthy holds a Bachelors degree in Human Resource Management from the Eli Broad College of Business at Michigan State University.  She is a member of the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM) and the Human Capital Institute (HCI) and has achieved her SPHR certification.\n', 'Elizabeth McCarthy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1675-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:21:16', '2011-10-17 14:21:16', '', 1675, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1677, 5, '2011-10-17 14:30:46', '2011-10-17 14:30:46', 'Ms. Cosper joined Futurestep in August 2010 as a Configuration Analyst in the virtual Support Center working with multiple clients on various ATS platforms.  \r\n\r\nMs. Cosper provides tier one and tier two support to global clients utilizing an online customer relationship management system. Ms. Cosper supports candidates, recruiters, and system administrators with system issues, configurations, system testing and enhancements.  She has been instrumental in developing and documenting best practices for tier one and tier two support analysts.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Cosper supported numerous clients in the Applicant Tracking Systems’ space as an Implementation Consultant and Analyst for a global RPO firm.  In this role she conducted product demonstrations, led requirements gathering sessions and completed system configurations to meet client specifications.  She also provided post implementation system administration support.   \r\n\r\nBefore moving into the technology side of Recruitment, Ernie served as a Client Services Specialist (HR Specialist) at large metropolitan Health Care Organization where she was responsible for Human Resources service delivery, planning and implementation of HR initiatives, policies and practices in client organizations.  Ms. Cosper has also served as a Senior Recruiter for an international telecom company and as a SAP Resource Manager for an international SAP partner. Ms. Cosper began her professional career as a supervisor for operational and HR personnel for a national managed care and medical cost containment company in both Louisiana and Texas.\r\n \r\nMs. Cosper holds a Bachelor of Liberal Studies from Loyola University in New Orleans, Louisiana and received her SPHR in 2003. ', 'Ernestine Cosper', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ernestine-cosper', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:30:46', '2011-10-17 14:30:46', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1677', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1678, 1, '2011-10-12 18:38:52', '2011-10-12 18:38:52', 'Recruitment process outsourcing (RPO) offers the optimal solution to managing challenging resourcing requirements in today‚Äôs volatile economies.\r\n\r\nOperational benefits include process efficiencies and access to expert, flexible, scalable resources. Our clients see significant financial benefits, not just in terms of reduction in cost and time to hire, but through much greater visibility and control of recruitment costs. And working in partnership with our clients we are able to help them realise strategic benefits such as implementing a proactive workforce planning process, reinforcing their employer brand and increasing the quality of talent brought into the business.\r\n\r\nFuturestep has over 13 years experience in developing and building bespoke outsourced recruitment solutions that make a positive commercial impact to our clients. We have an extensive global network, in-depth sector expertise and a wide range of complementary consulting solutions. We employ only the most experienced and innovative recruitment professionals, and as a part of the Korn/Ferry group, incorporate the most sophisticated and developed recruitment tools and expertise into our processes.', 'Recruitment Process Outsourcing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-72', '', '', '2011-10-12 18:38:52', '2011-10-12 18:38:52', '', 11, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1679, 5, '2011-10-17 14:29:55', '2011-10-17 14:29:55', 'Ms. Cosper joined Futurestep in August 2010 as a Configuration Analyst in the virtual Support Center working with multiple clients on various ATS platforms.  \n\nMs. Cosper provides tier one and tier two support to global clients utilizing an online customer relationship management system. Ms. Cosper supports candidates, recruiters, and system administrators with system issues, configurations, system testing and enhancements.  She has been instrumental in developing and documenting best practices for tier one and tier two support analysts.\n\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Cosper supported numerous clients in the Applicant Tracking Systems’ space as an Implementation Consultant and Analyst for a global RPO firm.  In this role she conducted product demonstrations, led requirements gathering sessions and completed system configurations to meet client specifications.  She also provided post implementation system administration support.   \n\nBefore moving into the technology side of Recruitment, Ernie served as a Client Services Specialist (HR Specialist) at large metropolitan Health Care Organization where she was responsible for Human Resources service delivery, planning and implementation of HR initiatives, policies and practices in client organizations.  Ms. Cosper has also served as a Senior Recruiter for an international telecom company and as a SAP Resource Manager for an international SAP partner. Ms. Cosper began her professional career as a supervisor for operational and HR personnel for a national managed care and medical cost containment company in both Louisiana and Texas.\n \nMs. Cosper holds a Bachelor of Liberal Studies from Loyola University in New Orleans, Louisiana and received her SPHR in 2003. ', 'Ernestine Cosper', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1677-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:29:55', '2011-10-17 14:29:55', '', 1677, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1680, 5, '2011-10-17 14:35:53', '2011-10-17 14:35:53', 'Ms. Matthews, Consulting Director for Futurestep, has more than 12 years of experience on consulting projects both globally and regionally helping clients improve the effectiveness of their Talent Acquisition and HR systems. \r\n\r\nMs. Matthews is a goal-oriented, results-driven leader with a strong background in talent management/talent acquisition systems, change management, project management, process analysis, workforce planning and business process outsourcing.\r\n \r\nFormerly, Ms. Matthews was a Senior Recruiting Manager providing management and business consulting expertise to internal clients globally in the area of talent management/acquisition. Prior to a Sr. Recruiting Manager, she was a Project Lead, Global HR Solutions at ACS. In this role, Ms. Matthews was responsible for managing and implementing ATS for her clients. This work included implementation of standardized integrations, identifying resources required and duration to execute against financial benefits, risks and impacts of doing the implementations. Ms. Matthews also held the roles of Human Resources Manager and Lead Recruiter with previous employers.\r\n\r\nMs. Matthews holds a Bachelor of Arts in Social Work from St. Edwards University in Austin, TX.\r\n', 'Kenyatta Matthews', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kenyatta-matthews', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:39:06', '2011-10-17 14:39:06', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1680', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1681, 1, '2011-10-17 14:30:30', '2011-10-17 14:30:30', 'In a volatile and fiercely competitive world, businesses and organizations of all kinds need to identify, recruit and retain talent with impact. Futurestep Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO) provides the optimal solution.\r\n\r\nRPO delivers a number of key benefits:\r\n• Better and more cost effective processes\r\n• Reductions in cost and time to hire and more control over both\r\n• Access to scalable, flexible talent resources\r\n• Enhanced employer brand and corporate reputation\r\n• More responsive workforce planning\r\n\r\nOver the past 13 years we’ve established ourselves as RPO specialists, delivering solutions that make a positive commercial impact for our clients. We’ve extended our global network and the breadth of our offer to cover almost every industry sector and specialist functions, with a particular focus on mid and senior level managerial technical talent.\r\n\r\nFuturestep delivers talent with impact because we invest in the best: the best professionals in our industry and through Korn/Ferry the most advanced recruitment tools and processes – standardized to suit the needs of multinational organizations and yet sensitive to local characteristics.', 'Recruitment Process Outsourcing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-73', '', '', '2011-10-17 14:30:30', '2011-10-17 14:30:30', '', 11, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
