(1711, 5, '2011-10-17 15:04:11', '2011-10-17 15:04:11', 'Ms. Potts is a Principal Consultant at Futurestep, with over twenty years experience in the professional services sector. Ms. Potts’ expertise resides in assisting organizations to successfully align their business strategies with their talent management strategies.  Her experience spans organizational alignment, workforce planning, succession planning, assessment methodologies and leadership development.  She has also created and delivered large scale change management strategies for pre-merger and post-merger initiatives. \r\n\r\nPreviously, Ms. Potts served as managing director of a talent management consulting firm and specialized in developing process oriented talent management business solutions, performance-based executive development programs and competency modeling.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, Ms. Potts served as vice president of global business for a behavioral assessment organization. During that time, Ms. Potts developed a global integration strategy for Fortune 500 clients.   \r\n\r\nMs. Potts brings a hands-on approach to her clients. She possesses unique business expertise, strong observation skills and a strategic understanding of organizational dynamics.  Ms. Potts is focused on delivering creative talent management solutions to her clients that are  measurable and sustainable.\r\n\r\nMs. Potts secured a Masters Certification in business management from the Wharton School of business, University of Pennsylvania and a Bachelor of Arts degree in psychology from Monmouth University.', 'Linda Potts', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'linda-potts', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:04:11', '2011-10-17 15:04:11', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1711', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
