(1729, 5, '2011-10-17 15:20:22', '2011-10-17 15:20:22', 'Mr. Lopez joined Futurestep in 2003 as a Project Manager and in 2005, he was promoted to his current role as Director of Human Resources.  \r\n\r\nAs the North American Director of Human Resources and as a strategic business partner, Mr. Lopez oversees and provides direction for all aspects of Human Resources and field operations to include: performance management, employee relations, compensation management, recruitment and staffing.  Mr. Lopez has over twenty years experience in the areas of talent acquisition and human resources. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurstep, Mr. Lopez was the Area Operations Manager/ExxonMobil for Kelly Services. His responsibilities included account management and all service delivery for their South Central Texas office facilities to include Chemical, Refining and Plastics plants. \r\n\r\nMr. Lopez has served in the following roles at: CORESTAFF Services- HR and Recruiting Manager, Bank of America- Employment Manager and Talent Tree Staffing/Hestair Technology- Onsite Client Manager and Technical Recruiter\r\n\r\nMr. Lopez holds a Bachelors of Arts degree in Psychology and a minor in Philosophy from the University of St. Thomas in Houston, Texas. \r\n', 'Julian Lopez ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'julian-lopez', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:23:52', '2011-10-17 15:23:52', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1729', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1731, 1, '2011-10-17 15:15:47', '2011-10-17 15:15:47', '<p>A competitive manufacturing sector is now considered an essential prerequisite for sustainable prosperity, but over the past few years we have witnessed a significant shift in the global economy  - with industrial growth in emerging economies gaining pace while industrial capacity in mature economies contracts but becomes increasingly productive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One consequence of this shift is that engineering and other industrial firms are shifting their talent capacity to support a move into emerging markets. This shift demands greater talent mobility and has seen talent community become increasingly global in nature, with project leadership and business impact skills at a premium.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOur Industrial team has the expertise to help businesses access the technical and commercial talent they need to succeed in a changing world. The team’&#39;s experience spans key sectors, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Construction</li>\r\n	<li>Infrastructure</li>\r\n	<li>Oil and gas</li>\r\n	<li>Energy</li>\r\n	<li>Automotive</li>\r\n	<li>Manufacturing</li>\r\n	<li>Defense and Aerospace</li>\r\n	<li>Mining and transportation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>', 'Industrial', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '369-revision-6', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:15:47', '2011-10-17 15:15:47', '', 369, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1732, 6, '2011-10-17 15:15:32', '2011-10-17 15:15:32', 'LOS ANGELES, October 10, 2011 - Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today announced the appointment of Jaishankar (Jai) Adhinarayanan as VP, Global Service Management Centers.\n\nMr. Jaishankar joins Futurestep with an incredible depth of experience in the management of service organizations, with a concentration on start-ups and process improvement of HRO, BPO and ITES operations. Most recently, he was the General Manager (Operations/Finance) of Risesmart in India, where he was heading service delivery for the India Center.\nPrevious roles include Transformation Leader and Delivery Project Executive at IBM, driving transition, delivery and process redesign within their HRO Operations using lean six sigma practices, and he has also worked in related roles for Exult and ACS. Mr. Jaishankar has spent time working in EMEA, the U.S. and Asia and is a Certified Six Sigma Master Black Belt.\n\n“Our Service Management Centers (SMCs) around the world are a critical and valued part of the Futurestep infrastructure. The capabilities and expertise centered in our SMCs allow us to provide sophisticated and efficient recruitment solutions that deliver real impact to our clients around the world. Today, we have six global SMCs; in Houston, Shanghai, Bangalore, Warsaw, Auckland, and Sydney and are intending to open a seventh in 2012 in Buenos Aires. Jai’s appointment and deep expertise will undoubtedly further enhance the breadth and quality of services provided by our SMCs. I am delighted he has chosen to join the Futurestep team,” said Futurestep’s Chief Executive Officer Byrne Mulrooney.\n\nMr. Jaishankar said, “It gives me great pleasure to be a part of the Futurestep family. This is a great opportunity to bring together cutting-edge technology and standardized global operations with the expertise of the Futurestep team. I am looking forward to further developing our capabilities to provide transformational solutions to our clients.”\n\nAbout Futurestep\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions; offering fully customized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs. Our clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure, proprietary competency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to measure and optimize business impact.\nAs a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements; from RPO and project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class capability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify, attract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.futurestep.com">www.futurestep.com</a>.\n\nAbout Korn/Ferry International\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based in Los Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit <a href="http://www.kornferry.com/">http://www.kornferry.com</a> for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and <a href="http://www.kornferryinstitute.com/">http://www.kornferryinstitute.com</a> for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'FUTURESTEP APPOINTS JAI ADHINARAYANAN TO RUN GLOBAL SERVICE MANAGEMENT CENTERS', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1720-revision-6', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:15:32', '2011-10-17 15:15:32', '', 1720, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
