(1743, 5, '2011-10-17 15:33:31', '2011-10-17 15:33:31', 'Bill Gilbert is Vice President & General Manager, Search, for the U.S., where he is responsible for leading the development and delivery of effective professional recruitment solutions for Futurestep. He has been working with clients to identify top talent as well as broader talent management initiatives for over fifteen years.\r\n\r\nPrior to his current role, Mr. Gilbert oversaw client development in the U.S., helping to build and maintain key client relationships for Futurestep’s Strategic Talent Acquisition solutions. He was also Office Director for Futurestep Atlanta where he was responsible for all aspects of performance, including client relations, search execution and staff development.\r\n\r\nPrior to Futurestep, he was with an international executive search firm where he worked with several high-profile clients, principally in the consumer products, financial services, industrial and professional services industries.\r\n\r\nBefore entering the executive search profession, Mr. Gilbert was Chief Financial Officer of Party America, Inc., a specialty retailer. Previously, he was Chief Administrative and Financial Officer with Treasure House Stores, Inc., a venture capital-backed turnaround. He also served as Chief Financial Officer for Silk Greenhouse, Inc. in Tampa. He began his career with KPMG\r\n\r\nMr. Gilbert earned a Bachelor’s degree in Accounting from Florida State University. \r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Bill Gilbert', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '1743', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:33:41', '2011-10-17 15:33:41', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1743', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1744, 6, '2011-09-13 15:28:11', '2011-09-13 15:28:11', '<strong>Los Angeles, September, 13, 2011</strong> - Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today announced two significant appointments in its consulting solutions team; Doug Rippey as Global Practice Leader, Workforce Planning, and Dave Marzo as General Manager for Consulting Solutions in North America.\r\n\r\nWith responsibility for the entire global Workforce Planning offering, Mr. Rippey will be tasked with providing best-in-class workforce planning solutions to Futurestep clients across the world. Prior to joining the Futurestep business, Mr. Rippey worked at Towers Watson for over ten years, where in 2003 he was one of the initial four consultants to form the Workforce Planning practice.  Futurestep’s Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Byrne Mulrooney said about the appointment, “Since joining the Futurestep business late last year, Mr. Rippey has been instrumental in helping Futurestep build and\r\nenhance its workforce planning offerings, supporting several strategically important global accounts. His appointment as Global Practice Leader, the first of its kind at Futurestep, is a significant step in the expansion of our global consulting capabilities.\r\n\r\nTaking on the role of General Manager for Consulting in North America, Mr Marzo will be responsible for overall leadership, accountability, and growth of Futurestep''s consulting offerings throughout the United States and Canada.\r\nMr. Marzo has an extensive consulting background, most recently supporting Korn/Ferry’s integrated goto-market strategy and working with some of the Firm’s major accounts. The new role for Mr.Marzo sees him work directly with Futurestep’s CEO, Byrne Mulrooney to guide the development and integration of the businesses consulting offering across the highly competitive North America region.\r\n\r\nBill Sebra, President of Futurestep North America said, “We are committed to providing our clients with comprehensive and fully integrated solutions to their talent requirements. Dave’s appointment will ensure our North American clients benefit from the full depth and breadth in expertise of our global consulting capabilities.”\r\n\r\n Both Mr. Rippey and Mr. Marzo start their respective roles with immediate effect.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Futurestep</strong>\r\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions; offering fully customized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs. Our clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure, proprietary competency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to measure and optimize business impact.\r\nAs a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements; from RPO and project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class capability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify, attract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.futurestep.com/">www.futurestep.com</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Korn/Ferry International</strong>\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based in Los Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit <a href="http://www.kornferry.com/">http://www.kornferry.com</a> for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and <a href="http://www.kornferryinstitute.com/">http://www.kornferryinstitute.com</a> for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'Futurestep Appoints Doug Rippey and Dave Marzo to Consulting Solutions Leadership Roles', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'futurestep-appoints-doug-rippey-and-dave-marzo-to-consulting-solutions-leadership-roles', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:28:37', '2011-10-17 15:28:37', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=1744', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(1746, 1, '2011-10-17 15:13:26', '2011-10-17 15:13:26', '<p>The global technology market is the fastest moving sector in the world, with businesses of all sizes fighting to attract and nurture the talent they need to become the market leaders of the future.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur Technology team offers a wealth and breadth of expertise unmatched in our industry: seasoned recruitment professionals and specialists with priceless ‘&#39;client-side’&#39; experience. Utilising state-of-the-art recruitment tools and processes, the team covers a wide range of sub-sectors – software, hardware, telecommunications, networking, technology consulting, professional services and media services – recruiting across all roles and functions in each. The team frequently helps businesses to recruit senior executives, including regional vice presidents, managing directors and IT directors and into:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operations</li>\r\n<li>Marketing</li>\r\n<li>HR</li>\r\n<li>Sales</li>\r\n<li>Finance</li>\r\n<li>Technology</li>\r\n<li>Procurement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our clients range from blue-chip multinationals through to SMEs or small start-ups and include some of the best-known technology brands in the world today. They choose us because they know we can consistently deliver the very best talent.</p>\r\n', 'Technology', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '373-revision-9', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:13:26', '2011-10-17 15:13:26', '', 373, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
