(1762, 6, '2011-06-29 15:36:50', '2011-06-29 15:36:50', '<strong>LONDON, JUNE 29, 2011</strong> – Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry Company (NYSE: KFY) has announced advancements and additions to its EMEA organization to address growing demand for its solutions in the region. Mark Lee has been appointed Managing Director, EMEA RPO, Cathy Desmedt as Managing Director, EMEA Project Recruiting and Jonathan Brown has joined the company as Director, EMEA Solutions Architecture. In addition, Futurestep has formally opened\r\nan office in Geneva.\r\n\r\nAs Managing Director, EMEA RPO, Mark Lee oversees all facets of Futurestep’s RPO business across EMEA, including execution of local RPO strategies, and expansion and optimization of Futurestep’s business portfolio in the region. Over the past two years, he has led the growth of Futurestep’s U.K. RPO operations, drawing on his deep experience in the industry to drive business growth. Prior to Futurestep, he served as a business leader for a major U.K. provider of consulting and outsourced services in recruitment and RPO.\r\n\r\nComplementing its RPO business and leadership expansion, Futurestep has appointed Cathy Desmedt as Managing Director EMEA Project Recruiting. In her role, Mrs. Desmedt will oversee the continued development of Project-Based Recruitment solutions and related search projects, talent pooling, and graduate recruiting offerings. Ms. Desmedt has more than 15 years experience in the HR Consultancy business, developing and managing large and complex talent\r\nacquisition solutions across continental Europe. Prior to joining Futurestep, Mrs. Desmedt was a consultant with the Havas Communication Group, advising global customers in designing and implementing assessment and recruitment solutions for MBA’s and international talent. She is fluent in French, English and Dutch and holds a Master in Political Sciences from the Free University of Brussels, Belgium.\r\n\r\nBased in London as Director, EMEA Solutions Architecture, Jonathan Brown will focus on the identification, design and acquisition of RPO contracts for the region. Before joining Futurestep, he was head of assessment &amp; selection and head of client services at global RPO provider Alexander Mann Solutions (AMS), where he led solutions delivery for a number of multi-national organizations. Prior to AMS, Mr. Brown worked as an associate director at RPO and talent management specialist Reflect, part of The Hydrogen Group. In addition, he spent five years at the management consultancy SHL Group where he delivered consulting to public and FTSE 100 companies. Jonathan holds a Masters of Science (MSc) in Organisational Psychology from the University of London.\r\n\r\nFinally, to support the growth of its solutions business in the region, Futurestep has opened an office in Geneva. In addition to his current role as Director of the Futurestep Lyon office, Jean-Christophe Puget will oversee the opening and operation of the Geneva location.\r\n\r\n“Futurestep is experiencing significant demand for its RPO and Project-Based Recruitment solutions across the EMEA region,” said Joel Perrenoud, President, Futurestep EMEA. “The growth and advancement of our leadership and operational team addresses that demand, and it enables us to deliver the business impact that our clients come to expect from a world-class provider of recruitment solutions.”', 'Futurestep Expands EMEA Leadership And Operations', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'futurestep-expands-emea-leadership-and-operations', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:40:28', '2011-10-17 15:40:28', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=1762', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(1763, 5, '2011-10-17 15:40:52', '2011-10-17 15:40:52', 'Ms. Kaplan is the Search Operations Leader for Futurestep’s Search Practice in the US and is based in Dallas, TX. She offers twenty years of experience managing full life cycle recruiting with proven expertise in talent acquisition, operations, and process improvement. She works closely with the Managing Consultants to ensure exceptional service delivery and leverages team capabilities to maximize results.  \r\n \r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Kaplan was the Vice President of Talent Acquisition for a start-up retained search firm, where she leveraged her broad talent management understanding to create and implement end-to-end  talent acquisition strategies attuned to the complexities of the virtual global economy. Ms. Kaplan built the operations model for the firm and managed the talent acquisition team. \r\n \r\nPreviously, she worked at Lee Hecht Harrison providing overall leadership and coordination of job development for clients in career transition. Before joining Lee Hecht Harrison, Ms. Kaplan was a Founder and Director of Operations and Training for HirePotential, a national consulting and employment firm that worked with corporations to hire, integrate and retain people with disabilities. Early in her career, Ms. Kaplan held various positions in recruitment, management, field operations, and training and development. \r\n\r\nMs. Kaplan received a Masters of Science in Human Relations and Business from Amberton University in Dallas and her Bachelor of Arts in Psychology from the University of Texas at Austin. \r\n', 'Allison Kaplan', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'allison-kaplan', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:43:44', '2011-10-17 15:43:44', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1763', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
