(1770, 6, '2011-05-10 15:42:36', '2011-05-10 15:42:36', '<strong>Los Angeles, May 10, 2011</strong> - Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today announced that it has appointed Roberto Spuri as Managing Director of its Latin American business. Mr. Spuri will be responsible for driving the growth of Futurestep’s successful Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), consulting and retained search services across the region.\r\n\r\nMr. Spuri brings to Futurestep a wealth of experience in the HR outsourcing arena. He joins the company from Convergys, which was recently acquired by NorthgateArinso, where he led the organization’s client services division in Brazil. In this role, he oversaw all facets of client relationship management, service delivery management and business growth, spanning multiple countries across the region and encompassing a full scope of HR services.\r\n\r\nPrior to Convergys, Mr. Spuri led strategy deployment for Accenture HR Services’ Latin America region, acting as a solution architect. As leader of the company’s Curitiba/PR HR Shared Service Center, he was in charge of launching the business, including operational design, systems implementation, infrastructure activation, personal hiring, service delivery management and change management programs related to Personal Administration, Benefits and Payroll services. While at Accenture, he also led the deployment and implementation of an insourced HR Shared Service Center for a leading industrial company in Venezuela.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Accenture, Mr. Spuri held successful HR roles across multiple industries. As HR Manager at DirecTV do Brasil Ltda., he played a critical part in the implementation of an ERP HR system for all Latin America Operations, as well as labor relations activity. At Philip Morris do Brasil, his areas of focus began with compensation and quickly grew to HR management. Prior to Philip Morris, he held compensation and HR management roles at Eurofarma Pharmaceutical Company, and Oxiteno S.A. – Chemical/Petrochemical.\r\n\r\n“Futurestep is experiencing a steady growth in demand for its global RPO and recruitment solutions in all regions, including Latin America,” said Byrne Mulrooney, chief executive officer of Futurestep. “Roberto’s addition to our leadership team underscores our commitment to building on our extensive global infrastructure and expertise, and to providing solutions that deliver the business impact our clients have come to expect.”\r\n\r\nSergio Averbach, president, South America for Korn/Ferry, added, “Roberto has deep industry experience and a record of accomplishment in human capital outsourcing operations. He is a great addition to the Futurestep Korn/Ferry business in Latin America, and we look forward to continued success as he leads the growth of our Futurestep recruitment solutions business in the region.“\r\n\r\n<strong>About Futurestep</strong>\r\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions; offering fully customized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs. Our clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure, proprietary competency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to measure and optimize business impact. As a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements; from RPO and project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class capability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify, attract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.futurestep.com/">www.futurestep.com</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Korn/Ferry International</strong>\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based in Los Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit <a href="http://www.kornferry.com/">http://www.kornferry.com</a> for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and <a href="http://www.kornferryinstitute.com/">http://www.kornferryinstitute.com</a> for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'Futurestep Appoints Roberto Spuri As Managing Director, Latin America', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'futurestep-appoints-roberto-spuri-as-managing-director-latin-america', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:46:50', '2011-10-17 15:46:50', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=1770', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(1771, 5, '2011-10-17 15:40:52', '2011-10-17 15:40:52', 'Ms. Kaplan is the Search Operations Leader for Futurestep’s Search Practice in the US and is based in Dallas, TX. She offers twenty years of experience managing full life cycle recruiting with proven expertise in talent acquisition, operations, and process improvement. She works closely with the Managing Consultants to ensure exceptional service delivery and leverages team capabilities to maximize results.  \r\n \r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Kaplan was the Vice President of Talent Acquisition for a start-up retained search firm, where she leveraged her broad talent management understanding to create and implement end-to-end  talent acquisition strategies attuned to the complexities of the virtual global economy. Ms. Kaplan built the operations model for the firm and managed the talent acquisition team. \r\n \r\nPreviously, she worked at Lee Hecht Harrison providing overall leadership and coordination of job development for clients in career transition. Before joining Lee Hecht Harrison, Ms. Kaplan was a Founder and Director of Operations and Training for HirePotential, a national consulting and employment firm that worked with corporations to hire, integrate and retain people with disabilities. Early in her career, Ms. Kaplan held various positions in recruitment, management, field operations, and training and development. \r\n\r\nMs. Kaplan received a Masters of Science in Human Relations and Business from Amberton University in Dallas and her Bachelor of Arts in Psychology from the University of Texas at Austin. \r\n', 'Allison Kaplan', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1763-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:40:52', '2011-10-17 15:40:52', '', 1763, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
