(1783, 5, '2011-10-17 15:55:08', '2011-10-17 15:55:08', 'Mr. Langlois is a Project Leader based in Futurestep’s Montreal office. In his role, he is responsible for the leading the daily operations of large scale volume recruitment projects. \r\n\r\nSince joining Futurestep, Mr. Langlois led a project team to recruit multiple engineers and other technical professionals to a remote location in Northern Quebec for a global mining and manufacturing firm. In addition to his project leadership role, Mr. Langlois is responsible for leading highly specialized technical searches in disciplines of engineering and information technology. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Langlois has assumed leadership and recruitment roles in other Canadian and global recruitment firms. He has worked as an advisor to a range of clients in the manufacturing, mining and logistics sectors. \r\n\r\nMr. Langlois is fluently bilingual in French and English. He studied in Pharmacy from the Université de Montréal. \r\n', 'Sylvain Langlois ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1777-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-17 15:55:08', '2011-10-17 15:55:08', '', 1777, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1784, 5, '2011-10-17 16:06:20', '2011-10-17 16:06:20', 'Mr. Moore is a Managing Consultant for Futurestep, responsible for leading senior Accounting and Financial search assignments. With over fourteen years in recruitment, Mr. Moore has extensive experience in Executive Search, RPO and Corporate Recruitment. He has partnered with both Fortune 500 firms and start-ups and is recognized as a trusted advisor in talent acquisition. \r\n\r\nPrior to this Mr. Moore worked in Citigroup’s Headquarters and focused on talent acquisition for the Global Transaction Services business.  He joined Citi from a national executive search firm where he was a Managing Partner and ran the Accounting and Finance operation in New York.\r\n\r\nEarlier he started the search practice for TMP Worldwide, the parent company of Monster.com, and helped build out the Accounting and Finance division in the Northeast.  TMP spun off and created Hudson Global Resources and Mr. Moore joined their Workforce Solutions team.  He led the RPO engagement with Gartner, Inc. and was responsible for their talent acquisition in the Americas. \r\n\r\nMr. Moore graduated from Quinnipiac University in Connecticut with a Bachelor of Science in Business Management and a concentration in Human Resources\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Jonathan Moore', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jonathan-moore', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:06:20', '2011-10-17 16:06:20', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1784', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
