(1787, 6, '2011-09-12 11:43:21', '2011-09-12 11:43:21', 'LOS ANGELES, May 10, 2011 -- Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY), today announced that it has appointed Roberto Spuri as Managing Director of its Latin American business. Mr. Spuri will be responsible for driving the growth of Futurestep‚Äôs successful Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), consulting and retained search services across the region.\r\nMr. Spuri brings to Futurestep a wealth of experience in the HR outsourcing arena. He joins the company from Convergys, which was recently acquired by NorthgateArinso, where he led the organization‚Äôs client services division in Brazil. In this role, he oversaw all facets of client relationship management, service delivery management and business growth, spanning multiple countries across the region and encompassing a full scope of HR services.\r\nPrior to Convergys, Mr. Spuri led strategy deployment for Accenture HR Services‚Äô Latin America region, acting as a solution architect. As leader of the company‚Äôs Curitiba/PR HR Shared Service Center, he was in charge of launching the business, including operational design, systems implementation, infrastructure activation, personal hiring, service delivery management and change management programs related to Personal Administration, Benefits and Payroll services. While at Accenture, he also led the deployment and implementation of an insourced HR Shared Service Center for a leading industrial company in Venezuela.\r\nBefore joining Accenture, Mr. Spuri held successful HR roles across multiple industries. As HR Manager at DirecTV do Brasil Ltda., he played a critical part in the implementation of an ERP HR system for all Latin America Operations, as well as labor relations activity. At Philip Morris do Brasil, his areas of focus began with compensation and quickly grew to HR management. Prior to Philip Morris, he held compensation and HR management roles at Eurofarma Pharmaceutical Company, and Oxiteno S.A. 