(1792, 5, '2011-10-17 16:12:56', '2011-10-17 16:12:56', 'Ms. O''Brien is a Managing Consultant for Futurestep in Canada. She is responsible for developing client relationships and leads the execution and delivery of single search mandates. Ms. O’Brien is dedicated to placing top cross-functional professional talent in all industries, with a focus on the Financial Services, Technology and Manufacturing sectors. \r\n\r\nMs. O''Brien was previously the Director of Business Development at a boutique search firm and launched its technology practice.  She also spent nine years with IBM Canada Ltd., where she led client management, business development and marketing mandates. \r\n\r\nMs. O’Brien holds an Honors Bachelor''s Degree from the University of Western Ontario. \r\n\r\n', 'Kathleen O''Brien ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kathleen-obrien', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:12:56', '2011-10-17 16:12:56', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1792', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1793, 1, '2011-10-17 16:07:31', '2011-10-17 16:07:31', 'As a business that discovers, delivers and maximizes Talent with Impact for many of the world&#39;s most successful businesses – we understand only too well that &#39;personal development&#39; and &#39;career opportunity&#39; are both Top-Five drivers for joining and staying with an employer. We are using this understanding – and our access to state-of-the-art talent management and personal development processes and content via Lominger, a sister Korn/Ferry company – to build a thriving talent community inside our own business.\n\nAt the heart of this initiative is the creation of a unique digital profile or Careerbook for every single Futurestep employee: a personalized ‘&#39;tool’&#39; that enables them to build networks, access best practice and contribute to company-wide initiatives from the first day they join us. But Careerbook is much more than a &#39;tool&#39; – it is also the focus for colleagues&#39; career development throughout their time with us; the means by which they create and actively manage their own skills acquisition and development plan, in partnership with their line manager and with support from our HR team.\n\nIn simple terms, Careerbook gives every Futurestep colleague more control over the way and the means in which they grow with us. We believe that it represents a fundamental shift – a new &#39;paradigm&#39; – in the way a global business can support and foster colleague development.\n', 'Futurestep Careerbook', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1790-revision', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:07:31', '2011-10-17 16:07:31', '', 1790, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
