(1799, 5, '2011-10-17 16:20:13', '2011-10-17 16:20:13', 'As Director, Service Delivery, Eastern Canada, Melissa has overall accountability for the development of strategic client partnerships for search and project work in Eastern Canada. She also has responsibility for the allocation and management of resources, ensuring the quality and timely delivery of Futurestep’s recruitment offerings.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Melissa was a Project Leader on the Cameco project and a Senior Recruiter focusing on a variety of functional areas and industries.  \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Melissa worked at boutique recruitment firms focused on marketing, sales and operations roles  at the Director to CEO level.  Melissa started her career in IT and moved into training, marketing and project management roles at The Loyalty Group (AirMiles), BCE Emergis and an alumni portal start-up.\r\n\r\nMelissa graduated from Ryerson University with a Bachelors degree in Information Management.  She also graduated from Mohawk College with a Chemical Technical diploma.\r\n\r\n', 'Melissa Woodley', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'melissa-woodley', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:20:13', '2011-10-17 16:20:13', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1799', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
