(1803, 5, '2011-10-17 16:28:48', '2011-10-17 16:28:48', 'Mr. Kaplan is a Managing Consultant at Futurestep and has over 30 years experience in executive search consultancy and specializes in identifying top talent for medical device, diagnostics, biotechnology, pharmaceutical, and a broad range of Healthcare Services companies.  \r\n\r\nMr. Kaplan is a key member of the US Healthcare & Life Sciences practice for Futurestep which places mid management professionals across all management functions. He has placed hundreds of executives and is recognized as a trusted advisor, leveraging his broad industry knowledge and client experience to develop the appropriate recruitment strategies to support business goals. Mr. Kaplan provides strategic insight into the human capital market, executive talent assessment, executive compensation, and succession planning.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Mr. Kaplan served for six years as Client Partner in Korn/Ferry International’s New York office. As a member of the Global Life Sciences practice, he led engagements for leading companies within the Pharmaceutical, Biotechnology and Medical Device sectors. Many of his assignments were for senior executives at the President and CEO, CFO, CSO and Board level and functional leaders for sales, marketing, business development, research & development, finance, manufacturing, operations for financial-sponsored private and global public companies.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Korn/Ferry, he worked as a Client Partner with Ray & Berndtson in New York, where he served the life sciences industry, recruiting senior level general management and functional leaders in pharmaceutical, biotechnology clinical development, research and development, manufacturing, regulatory, finance and commercial marketing and sales leadership.\r\n\r\nMr. Kaplan holds a B.A. in Psychology from SUNY at Albany, New York. He resides in Westchester NY with his wife and three sons, two of whom are identical twins. He is an avid fly-fisherman and alpine skier.', 'Peter Kaplan', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'peter-kaplan', '', '', '2011-10-17 16:36:22', '2011-10-17 16:36:22', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1803', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
