(1809, 5, '2011-10-17 09:20:59', '2011-10-17 09:20:59', 'Ms. Brittain has over fifteen years in the recruiting industry. She brings extensive knowledge in the recruiting industry from managing RPOs and  building client relationships. She has executed and managed many different solutions in her career, including Compaq Computers, Continental Airlines, Kellogg, Hershey''s, Hexion Chemicals and Dell.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Brittain spent eleven years with Recruitment Enhancement Services an Omnicom Group Inc. company, as a Director, Client Services in its recruitment process outsourcing  division.\r\n\r\nMs. Brittain has experience in the areas of recruitment strategy, workflow process, client relationship, technology implementation, vendor relations, metric reports and best practices for achieving an organizations strategic vision and goals.\r\n \r\nAdditionally, Ms. Brittain has worked in various industries such as Consumer Packaged Goods, Specialty Chemicals, Manufacturing, Financial Services, Petroleum, Defense, Government, Information Technology, Engineering Construction,  and Advertising/Marketing.\r\n \r\nMs. Brittain graduated from Texas A&M in 1991 with a Bachelors degree.', 'Dena Brittain', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1593-revision-3', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:20:59', '2011-10-17 09:20:59', '', 1593, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1810, 5, '2011-10-17 09:20:24', '2011-10-17 09:20:24', 'Ms. Cade joined Futurestep in 2002 as a Recruiter quickly advancing to a Senior Recruiter and has served in a management role since 2004. \r\n\r\nCurrently, a Project Director in our Projects division, Ms. Cade is responsible for the deployment of recruitment management solutions, specializing in the Consumer and Industrial practices. She works with global and national clients utilizing best practices and the latest recruitment process efficiencies in each project she manages. \r\n\r\nFurther, Ms. Cade has managed global projects, client relationships and teams of centralized and decentralized Recruiters and Administrative staff.  \r\n\r\nMs. Cade has provided exceptional service delivery for Futurestep clients to include: Halliburton, General Mills, Kraft, Hilton, Rio Tinto, Yum Restaurants International, Goodyear Tire and Rubber, Palm, Morgan Stanley Smith Barney, Response Genetics and Wal-Mart.\r\n\r\nPrior to Joining Futurestep, Ms. Cade was a Senior Consultant with a boutique executive search firm focusing on the recruitment and placement of Executive and Mid-Management talent in the consumer, financial services, manufacturing, publishing and telecommunication industries. Ms. Cade excels at understanding client expectations, motivating her team to perform beyond those expectations, consulting with the client throughout the project and managing through continuous improvement. \r\n\r\nMs. Cade holds a Bachelor of Arts in Political Science from Western Illinois University in Macomb, Illinois.\r\n', 'Germayne Cade', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1595-revision-4', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:20:24', '2011-10-17 09:20:24', '', 1595, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1811, 5, '2011-10-17 09:18:56', '2011-10-17 09:18:56', 'Ms. Callaway joined Futurestep in 2011 as a Managing Consultant in the Dallas office. With over fifteen years of talent acquisition know-how, Ms. Callaway has served as a strategic partner to cliental ranging from start-ups to Fortune 100 corporations.  \r\n\r\nWorking in multiple verticals including Retail/Consumer, Technology, Industrial, Healthcare Services, Finance, and Consulting, Ms. Callaway is well versed in Corporate Infrastructure as well as Supply Chain and Logistics, but has particular expertise and passion around the Information Technology sector.  \r\n\r\nPrior to joining the firm, Ms. Callaway led the corporate recruiting team for a major retailer through multiple Information Technology transformations. Her corporate experience gives her unique perspective on how to aid corporations in attracting and retaining top talent.   \r\n\r\nEarlier, Ms. Callaway was founder and co-executive of a successful boutique search firm with a niche in technology consulting.  In this role she formed strategic alliances with her client organizations to successfully implement technical projects.  She has served as a consultant to numerous organizations on full life cycle recruiting including strategy architecture, process development, souring, selection, on-boarding, and retention.   \r\n\r\nMs. Callaway has served as an advisor to the CEO of Career Communications in their efforts to promote diversity in the work place and is a member of the National Association of Personnel Staffing and Women Business Enterprise National Council.\r\n', 'Dawn Callaway', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1597-revision-3', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:18:56', '2011-10-17 09:18:56', '', 1597, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1812, 5, '2011-10-17 09:30:38', '2011-10-17 09:30:38', 'Mr. Candland is client development manager for Futurestep with a focus on the Northeastern America. An expert at delivering RPO solutions to meet highly demanding client needs, he has extensive experience in culture and process customization and innovative candidate quality sourcing using advanced techniques and technologies. \r\n \r\nWith deep recruitment solutions experience in the financial services industry, Mr. Candland has been an executive sponsor and leader of RPO and managed staffing engagements for U.S. and international clients such as Deutsche Bank, UBS, Goldman Sachs, CitiGroup, American Express, Lehman Brothers, Bear Stearns, Standard Chartered Bank and Bridgewater.  \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Candland led the Managed Services Programs business of a US-focused specialty staffing solutions provider based in New York. Prior to that, he co-founded Advantage Human Resourcing and Advantage Global, both leading firms in staffing, contingent workforce management, executive search, RPO and MSP.  \r\n\r\nMr. Candland started his career as a securities market professional and investment banker in capital markets working for NASDAQ, Merrill Lynch and Dean Witter (Morgan Stanley). He earned an MBA from New York University and a BA from the University of Utah.  ', 'Steve Candland', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1607-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:30:38', '2011-10-17 09:30:38', '', 1607, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1813, 5, '2011-10-17 09:34:34', '2011-10-17 09:34:34', 'As Director, Service Delivery, Western Canada, Ms. Duncan has overall accountability for the development of strategic client partnerships for single search and project work in Western Canada. \r\n\r\nShe also has responsibility for the allocation and management of\r\nresources, ensuring the quality and timely delivery of Futurestep’s recruitment offerings.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Ms. Duncan was a senior recruiter here at Futurestep and has worked with organizations such as ICBC, BC Hydro, BCAA, Intrawest, Walter Energy, SIAST and The Capital Power Corporation.\r\n\r\nMs. Duncan has spent the past fourteen years working in international recruitment and talent management consulting. Prior to joining Futurestep she managed the Downtown Vancouver branch of an international recruitment firm leading a team responsible for\r\ntemporary, permanent and project recruitment offerings.\r\n\r\nPrior to coming to Canada, Ms. Duncan established the first regional IT organization, outside of London, for Badenoch and Clark, a leading UK recruitment firm, she also managed their finance division in the North West of England.\r\n\r\nMs. Duncan has extensive experience in operational and corporate recruitment in a variety of industries and has assisted her clients to develop strategic talent acquisition plans.\r\n\r\nMs. Duncan holds a Bachelor of Arts degree with honors from the University of Reading (UK), majoring in Politics and International Relations.', 'Samantha Duncan', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1609-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:34:34', '2011-10-17 09:34:34', '', 1609, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
