(1815, 5, '2011-10-17 09:39:16', '2011-10-17 09:39:16', 'Mr. Flavin leads Futurestep’s US RPO Implementation and Project solutions team based from our New York office.\r\n\r\nInitially Mr. Flavin joined Futurestep in 2009 as the Solutions Architect for the EMEA RPO business based in our London office. There he was responsible for the solution design and implementation for our global RPO solution for Newedge Group as well as the EMEA region of our global project solution for Dell.\r\n\r\nMr. Flavin is a recruitment professional, with fifteen years experience from agency, in-house recruitment, RPO and HR consulting businesses, and has worked in this field since graduating with a BA (Hons) Business Studies from Salford University, England.\r\n\r\nMr. Flavin has designed and delivered global RPO solutions for Credit Suisse and Numonyx based in the US as well as regional RPO solutions for Deloitte, Citigroup, UPM, Cap Gemini, Cable & Wireless and L’Occitane in EMEA.  He has also completed HR consulting assignments for, Barclays, Thales, KPMG and Local Government in the UK.\r\n\r\nPrior to his RPO career, Mr. Flavin worked as an in-house Recruitment Manager for Accenture, PricewaterhouseCoopers and Morse Group.', 'Paul Flavin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1611-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:39:16', '2011-10-17 09:39:16', '', 1611, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1816, 5, '2011-10-17 09:46:04', '2011-10-17 09:46:04', 'Ms. Gervais is a Program Manager for RPO Services Group in the U.S.  She is responsible for the design, development and deployment of recruitment solutions for a variety of private and public sector clients.   \r\n\r\nWith experience in managing teams of Talent Acquisition professionals to include Recruiters and Administrative staff, Ms. Gervais enjoys working closely with her clients; specifically managing customized solutions to meet client’s particular needs by utilizing best practices and the latest recruitment process efficiencies.\r\n\r\nMs. Gervais has been responsible for providing exceptional service delivery for Futurestep clients including: U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, Hilton Worldwide, Beckman Coulter, National Conservation Preservation Association, Volkswagen Group of America, and ICG Commerce. Prior to taking on her current responsibilities, Ms. Gervais was a Senior Recruiter with responsibility for search client deliverables.   \r\n\r\nBefore joining Futurestep in 2002, Ms. Gervais was a Team Lead with a staffing firm focusing on the recruitment and placement of IT professionals.  \r\n\r\nMs. Gervais excels at understanding client expectations, motivating her team to perform beyond those expectations, consulting with the client throughout the project and managing through continuous improvement.\r\n \r\nAdditionally, Ms. Gervais holds a Bachelor of Arts in Classical Greek from Dickinson College in Carlisle, PA.  She completed her Master of Divinity degree from Wesley Theological Seminary in May 2011.', 'Cynthia Gervais', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1613-revision-3', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:46:04', '2011-10-17 09:46:04', '', 1613, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1817, 5, '2011-10-17 09:50:35', '2011-10-17 09:50:35', 'Ms.Grillo is a Senior Recruiter, and part of the US Service Delivery RPO team.  In this capacity, Ms.Grillo is responsible for the execution of end-to-end recruitment services globally and nationwide. \r\n\r\nCurrently a member of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission RPO team, Ms.Grillo has successfully completed a recruiting project with the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Functionally, Ms.Grillo has executed searches in HR, Sales and Marketing, Government, Legal, Operations Finance, Accounting, HealthCare and Life Sciences.\r\n\r\nMs.Grillo excels at providing exceptional service to her clients including being a proactive consultant, delivering quality talent and superior candidate care.  Her ability to create innovative sourcing strategies to attract passive candidates is sought out by internal and external customers.   \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep in 2010, Ms.Grillo was a Recruiting Manager for the Healthcare Practice with Navigant Consulting for three years. During her tenure, she was responsible for the corporate recruitment process of multiple divisions of the HealthCare and Life Sciences practices and Diversity ERG initiatives. Ms.Grillo also spent over ten years working for organizations such as Yahoo! HotJobs, MicroStrategy, KaBoom!, and Elizabeth Glaser Pediatric AIDS foundation as a Talent Management and Recruitment solutions professional.\r\n\r\nMs.Grillo holds a Bachelor of Arts from Howard University. \r\n', 'Michelle Grillo', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1616-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:50:35', '2011-10-17 09:50:35', '', 1616, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1818, 5, '2011-10-17 09:52:54', '2011-10-17 09:52:54', 'Ms.Hanifen is a Managing Consultant for Futurestep’s US Search Practice and is based in Dallas, TX. Ms.Hanifen brings over twenty years of professional recruitment experience including Agency, Executive Search, and RPO businesses.  \r\n\r\nDuring her tenure with Futurestep, Ms.Hanifen has successfully executed search engagements across a wide range of verticals including Industrial, High Technology, Renewable Energy and Consumer Products.  \r\n\r\nWorking with an array of functions including Sales and Marketing, Engineering, Product Development, Environmental Health and Safety, Quality Assurance, Strategic Sourcing, Procurement,  Supplier Quality, Operations and Corporate Sustainability, Ms.Hanifen has developed an excellent reputation for client satisfaction and high quality candidate care. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep in 2008, Ms.Hanifen served as a Senior Recruiter at Recruitment Enhancement Services (RES), and Texas Instruments where she was responsible for full life cycle recruitment of senior level technical, business development, marketing, product development, scientific and operations personnel.  \r\n\r\nMs.Hanifen holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Liberal Arts and Sciences from DePaul University in Chicago, IL.', 'Cindy Hanifen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1618-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-17 09:52:54', '2011-10-17 09:52:54', '', 1618, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
