(1819, 5, '2011-10-17 10:06:00', '2011-10-17 10:06:00', 'Ms. Ho is a Managing Consultant and is responsible for client development and delivery of the Search business in Canada.\r\n\r\nMs. Ho excels at understanding client expectations, consulting with the client throughout the search process and delivering top talent through search process rigger and leveraging her extensive\r\nprofessional network.\r\n\r\nMs. Ho started at Futurestep as a Senior Recruiter with responsibility for single search client deliverables. She has been responsible for providing exceptional service delivery for Futurestep clients including: Insurance Corporation of BC, Viterra, New Gold, WhiteWater West Industries, British Columbia Automobile Association and Ballard Power Systems.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Ho’s brings over five years of diverse experience in various industries such as information technology, government agencies, crown corporations, professional services and hospitality/tourism; positions included senior leadership roles in human resources where she was responsible for key deliverables in talent acquisition, compensation and benefits management, training and development, performance management and various human resources and corporate communication system implementations.\r\n\r\nMs. Ho earned an MBA from Royal Roads University in 2006 and holds a\r\nBachelor of Arts in Applied Communications from Simon Fraser University. She also has completed executive education in leadership and negotiation from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania and Harvard Business School.', 'Nancy Ho', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1620-revision-5', '', '', '2011-10-17 10:06:00', '2011-10-17 10:06:00', '', 1620, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1820, 5, '2011-10-17 10:14:06', '2011-10-17 10:14:06', 'Ms. Johnson is a Senior Client Development Manager for Futurestep, joining the organization in 2009. Her role is to help organizations identify where strategic outsourced recruiting opportunities make sense for a variety of reasons, and focuses on how to best align objectives to solution offerings. \r\n\r\nMs. Johnson led and won the opportunity for Korn/Ferry Futurestep to become the exclusive global RPO provider for Cummins International, bringing global technology and process to the solution, and recruiting in over 50 key countries. Other clients under her efforts include Kraft Foods, Zurich NA, PwC, Jewish & St. Mary’s Hospital, U.S. Foodservice, to name a few.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Johnson was a Director of Global Client Management at Shaker Recruitment Advertising & Communications for 15 years, securing and overseeing Fortune 100 clients such as UPS, Target, Yum Brands, and HSBC. She directed the strategies for and managed teams executing on integrated media plans, as well as consulting on employment branding solutions.\r\n\r\nMs. Johnson is Chair of the Talent Acquisition Special Interest Group for The Human Resource Management Association of Chicago (HRMAC), sits on the programs committee for the Staffing Management Association of Chicago (SMA), and remains active in business associations such as The Executives Club of Chicago. Within her career, she contributed to recruitment industry articles publications, including Brandweek and Workforce Magazine. She has been a speaker at The Conference Board in NY, The National Restaurant Association Conference, and spoke with Lou Adler on his World Tour Summits and co-hosted numerous national webinars. \r\n\r\nAdditionally, Ms. Johnson holds a Bachelor of Science Degree in Marketing and Psychology from Elmhurst College, graduating Suma Cum Laude. ', 'Christine Johnson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1625-revision-3', '', '', '2011-10-17 10:14:06', '2011-10-17 10:14:06', '', 1625, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1822, 5, '2011-10-18 12:35:30', '2011-10-18 12:35:30', 'Mr. Simcock is Managing Director of Futurestep’s New Zealand business. He is also a member of Futurestep’s Global RPO Leadership team. \n\nWorking closely with Futurestep’s Asia Pacific management team and regional clients, Mr. Simcock enables the implementation and delivery of RPO projects and managed services across the region. In New Zealand, he leads consulting teams for Futurestep’s search, project recruitment, outsourcing and consulting services solutions.\n\nHaving joined Korn/Ferry International in New Zealand in 1998, Mr. Simcock''s role was spent focusing on senior executive appointments in the financial services, advanced technology and industrial sectors. Prior to Korn/Ferry, he spent five years in HR consulting in Tokyo, leading engagements for global emerging growth and Fortune 500 companies. \n\nMr. Simcock holds an MBA (Distinction) and a Bachelor of Arts from Victoria University and was on the Board of Advisors to the Otago University School of Business.\n', 'Nick Simcock', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1821-revision', '', '', '2011-10-18 12:35:30', '2011-10-18 12:35:30', '', 1821, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1823, 5, '2011-10-18 12:42:57', '2011-10-18 12:42:57', 'Ms. Tuffley is the Managing Director for Futurestep Australia. Since joining the Company in 2000, she has been instrumental in helping it become the market leader in Australia. As Managing Director, she is responsible for leading Futurestep’s entire portfolio of services including: projects, outsourcing, consulting and professional recruitment. \r\n\r\nPrior  to joining Futurestep, Ms. Tuffley worked for over 10 years in a variety of consulting and operational roles with a major Australian human resource consultancy, where she worked on consulting projects across APAC and EMEA.\r\n\r\nHer earlier career was in the health arena, practicing within both the public and private sector in Australia and the U.K. She also held tutoring and examining positions at the University of Queensland and Cumberland College.\r\n\r\nMs. Tuffley holds a Bachelor’s Degree from the University of Queensland, a Post Graduate Diploma from Cumberland College of Health Sciences and an Executive M.B.A. from the Australian Graduate School of Management, University of NSW.', 'Sue Tuffley', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sue-tuffley', '', '', '2011-10-18 12:42:57', '2011-10-18 12:42:57', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1823', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
