(1825, 5, '2011-10-18 13:03:48', '2011-10-18 13:03:48', 'Ms. Buck joined Futurestep in 2003. Most recently she has been responsible for leading the Asia Pacific implementation for a global RPO that will deliver over 2000 hires across the region in 2011. This included designing and implementing a global recruitment process with localised variations supported by Taleo 10 recruitment technology.   \r\n\r\nPrior to her relocation to Singapore she was based in Auckland, New Zealand and led Futurestep’s consulting engagement at Lumley General Insurance. The engagement focused on aligning the organisation’s key strategy of building capability across the entire organisation.\r\n\r\nMs. Buck led the design stream for the implementation of a client solution responsible for 2,000 hires per year across 30 locations in Australasia. She then took on the role of Operations Manager and then Recruitment Programme Manager working to deliver the sourcing and recruitment operations functions and volume recruitment projects. \r\n\r\nMs. Buck has assisted organisations across a variety of industry sectors and geographies, with the appointment of senior executives. Ms. Buck’s previous experience also includes implementation, change and project management for recruitment related initiatives.\r\n\r\nMs. Buck holds a BA in Human Geography and Business from Victoria University, Wellington.\r\n', 'Mandy Buck', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mandy-buck', '', '', '2011-10-18 13:03:48', '2011-10-18 13:03:48', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1825', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
