(1833, 5, '2011-10-18 14:12:39', '2011-10-18 14:12:39', 'Ms. Six is a Senior Talent Consultant for Training, based in Futurestep’s Shanghai office. As a People & Performance team member, she has the accountability for training operations and delivery for Asia (China, Hong Kong, Japan, Singapore and India). She drives continuous improvement initiatives for training as well as ongoing development of the training framework – including curriculum and delivery.\r\n \r\nDuring her studies, Ms Six took a strong interest in Talent Development. During her studies she gained professional experience in Brussels (Belgium) as a Human Resources Officer at ING Bank and then in Montreal (Canada) at the CFC Consulting Group as a Training Assistant. \r\n \r\nAfter graduation, Ms Six joined the Mentally Fit Institute (training and coaching firm) in Belgium for 3 years. She delivered training and coaching for junior staff and university students. Beside training delivery, she developed new training content and managed the internal and external communication of the firm. Following this experience, she took the chance to broaden her knowledge when she joined Deloitte Consulting (in Brussels and then Shanghai) as a Human Capital Consultant. She was part of the Organization and Change Team focusing on Change & Communication and Workforce & Talent Management for MNC clients. \r\n \r\nMs Six holds a Masters Degree in Organizational Psychology with a thesis on Team Coaching in the sport and corporate world. She is native speaker of French, speaks fluent Dutch and English and has a basic knowledge of Mandarin.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n', 'Pauline Six', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pauline-six', '', '', '2011-10-18 14:12:39', '2011-10-18 14:12:39', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1833', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
