(1837, 5, '2011-10-18 14:24:55', '2011-10-18 14:24:55', 'Ms. Wright is a Team Leader within Futurestep’s Service Management Center (SMC) in Shanghai. She is responsible for candidate resourcing strategies, project performance and reporting for a team of Sourcing Specialists.  Ms. Wright has a proven track-record in completing projects with tight timescales and in motivating teams to achieve results.  \r\n\r\nHer recent projects include market mapping exercises, market intelligence, multiple successful candidate searches for senior management positions, and an international compensation benchmarking review.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Wright has had a progressive ten-year career in London within the fields of Sales, Marketing and Project Management.  Her career started in EDF Energy, where her key responsibility was the account management of third party sales agencies in acquiring and processing new electricity, gas and telephone customers.  Ms. Wright then worked in the Project Office of Post Office Ltd to assist in effectively introducing new products and campaigns across the British Post Office network, including the launch of Financial Services Products and Home Phone services.  \r\n\r\nMore recently, she consulted to the comparison and switching website uSwitch.com as a Product Manager for Home Services.\r\n\r\nMs Wright’s strengths in project management, client liaison and team mobilization, in addition to her language skills, allow her to bring excellent outcomes to her Futurestep projects. She is highly regarded by her existing client base, who have provided strong customer feedback on her work. She has varied experience across the government, consumer, life science, industrial, technology, and financial services sectors, and her research work has covered South East Asia, China, and the UK. \r\n\r\nSince relocating to Shanghai, she has studied Mandarin at Jiao Tong University at the upper intermediate level.  \r\n\r\nMs. Wright graduated with a Bachelor of Arts (Hons) in International Business with German from Sheffield Hallam University in the United Kingdom. While in Shanghai, she studied Mandarin at Jiao Tong University at the upper intermediate level.  \r\n\r\n', 'Sarah Wright', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sarah-wright', '', '', '2011-10-18 14:24:55', '2011-10-18 14:24:55', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1837', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
