(1839, 5, '2011-10-18 15:45:40', '2011-10-18 15:45:40', 'Ms. Wang is a Managing Associate with Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company, based in Shanghai. As a member of the Industrial practice, Ms. Wang leverages almost 6 years of recruiting experience in placing middle and senior managers within the industry sectors as well as HR positions in multinational and Chinese organisations in Greater China. The positions include sales, marketing, manufacturing and supporting functions.\r\n\r\nShe was responsible for the Energy & Utility, Automotive & Transportation, Power, Electrical, Original Equipment Manufacturer and Medical Device industry sectors. In addition, she specialises hiring positions in the HR sectors. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Wang has worked in global recruitment firms and also a well-known local headhunting firm.\r\nMs. Wang had significant achievements with 20%-30% annual increase in sales volume and achieved Top Performer twice in her former executive agency. With experience successfully placing more than 70 individuals at a variety of levels including (and not exclusive to) Engineering Manager/Director, HR Manager/HR Director, Sales and Marketing Manager/ Director, and Operation Manager/Director.\r\n\r\nBorn and raised in Shanghai, Ms. Wang has a Bachelors Degree in Chemical Engineering from Shanghai Normal University. She speaks fluent Mandarin and English.\r\n', 'Sunny Wang', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sunny-wang', '', '', '2011-10-18 15:46:52', '2011-10-18 15:46:52', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1839', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1840, 4, '2011-10-18 15:00:37', '2011-10-18 15:00:37', 'Lyn Currie to Lead RPO and Karen Wong to Lead Search Business,\r\nSupporting Continued Growth in the Region.\r\n\r\nLOS ANGELES, January 11, 2010 – Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company today\r\nannounced two new appointments in its Canadian business leadership. Lyn Currie has been named as Vice President and General Manager of its RPO and Recruitment Solutions business, and Karen Wong has been named as Vice President and General Manager of its Markets business. The addition of the two new dedicated leadership roles comes as Futurestep expands its Canadian organization to meet further growth in demand for its Strategic Talent Acquisition solutions.\r\n\r\n“Over the past decade, Futurestep has developed a record of success providing tremendous value through its recruitment solutions for Canadian clients,” said Futurestep CEO Byrne Mulrooney. “Through the leadership of Lyn Currie and Karen Wong, we look forward to further growth in our RPO, Project Recruitment and Markets business in across the North America region.”\r\n\r\nAs Vice President and General Manager of the RPO and Project Recruitment solutions business for Futurestep in Canada, Lyn Currie has overall leadership and accountability for the strategic direction, development and growth in those areas. Previously, as Practice Leader for Futurestep she was responsible for leading and managing business development and key client relationships both nationally and globally.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Currie was Managing Director of a global technology recruitment and outsourcing consulting firm where she was instrumental in growing the business and in delivering strategic projects for clients. Over the course of her career she was responsible for leading several divisions of the organization, advising clients on recruitment strategies, and delivering customized talent management solutions for key national accounts. Ms. Currie holds an honors bachelor''s degree from the University of Western Ontario.\r\n\r\nAs Vice President and General Manager of the Markets business for Canada, Karen Wong will oversee strategic direction, development and growth for its Markets (Midlevel Search) solutions. This responsibility encompasses operational oversight and engagement management. Since 2006, Ms. Wong has been Service Delivery Leader for Futurestep, with involvement in solutions across the business, including recruitment, project management and service delivery.\r\n\r\nBefore joining the company in 2006, Ms. Wong spent over a decade working abroad in Hong Kong and New York City, initially as an Audit Manager with Price Waterhouse Hong Kong. She then joined Michael Page Hong Kong, where she built and ran its largest division in financial services and helped them achieve recognition as the top recruitment consultancy in Asia within two years of its start up. Ms. Wong subsequently transferred to their New York office and established a highly successful front office banking practice. Ms. Wong holds a Graduate Diploma in Public Accountancy and a Bachelor’s Degree in Commerce from McGill University. She is a Chartered Accountant.\r\n\r\nAbout Futurestep\r\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions;offering fully customized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs.\r\n\r\nOur clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure,proprietary competency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to measure and optimize business impact.\r\n\r\nAs a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements;from RPO and project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class capability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify, attract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.futurestep.com/">www.futurestep.com</a>.\r\n\r\nAbout Korn/Ferry International\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based in Los Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit <a href="http://www.kornferry.com/">http://www.kornferry.com</a> for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and <a href="http://www.kornferryinstitute.com/">http://www.kornferryinstitute.com</a> for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'FUTURESTEP EXPANDS RPO AND RECRUITMENT LEADERSHIP IN CANADA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'futurestep-expands-rpo-and-recruitment-leadership-in-canada', '', '', '2011-10-18 15:00:37', '2011-10-18 15:00:37', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=1840', 0, 'press', '', 0),
