(1858, 5, '2011-10-18 15:56:40', '2011-10-18 15:56:40', 'Based in Shanghai, Mr. Chia is responsible for customising talent acquisition solutions for his clients and to oversee the implementation and delivery of these solutions.\r\n\r\nMr. Chia has a track record of implementing and managing two large-scaled global workforce outsourcing programs; one for an IT solutions company and another for a global company in the consumer electronics industry.  These solutions were deployed into China, Hong Kong, Taiwan, Japan and Korea. \r\n\r\nPrevious engagements included managing an outsourcing delivery team to provide HR administration, compensation and benefits processing for multi-national companies in North Asia.\r\n\r\nPrior to relocating to Shanghai, Mr. Chia was based in Singapore working in the consulting industry where he led an outsourcing unit to deliver IT and HR function support to an international tier one airlines.  \r\n\r\nMr. Chia’s previous experiences included implementing and managing large-scaled ERP (Enterprise Resources Planning) programs in the South East Asian region.  He was also responsible for change management and process re-engineering of these engagements. \r\n\r\nWorking extensively in global projects and coordinating with business partners from various geographic regions has strengthened Mr. Chia’s ability in understanding and addressing regional  talent management issues and cultural differences.\r\n\r\nOriginally from Singapore, Mr. Chia holds an MBA from University of London and a Bachelors Degree in Computer Science from University of California  and he is fluent in English, Chinese and Cantonese.\r\n', 'Loy Tong Chia ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'loy-tong-chia', '', '', '2011-10-18 15:56:40', '2011-10-18 15:56:40', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1858', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
