(1860, 5, '2011-10-18 16:00:24', '2011-10-18 16:00:24', 'Based in Shanghai, Mr. Li is a Managing Associate with Futurestep. He joined Futurestep in 2005 as an Associate Consultant and was promoted to his current role in 2007 responsible for strategic talent acquisition. He has experience in Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO) and has worked on several projects including on-site representation.\r\n\r\nA member of the Industrial practice, Mr. Li leverages ten years of recruiting experience in placing middle and senior managers within the mechanical, construction machinery, chemical, oil, new energy and consumer sectors in multinational and Chinese organisations in Greater China. The positions include sales, marketing, manufacturing and supporting functions.\r\n\r\nAccording to a Customer Satisfaction Index for January and April of 2009, conducted by a third party consulting firm, Mr. Li was one of the top performers within Futurestep globally.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Li was an associate consultant in a NASDAQ listed human resource company. There, he successfully recruited over 100 individuals in the manufacturing sector, from managers to senior directors, for a leading global organization. Before that, Mr. Li worked with a local executive search firm as an associate consultant within the manufacturing sector, focusing on sourcing and selecting senior candidates. \r\n\r\nPrior to his executive search career, Mr. Li worked as a technical engineer with an equipment provision company in Beijing. \r\n\r\nBorn and raised in Beijing, Tony has a Bachelor Degree in Mechanical Engineering from Beijing Polytechnic University. He speaks fluent Mandarin and English. \r\n', 'Tony Li ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tony-li', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:02:50', '2011-10-18 16:02:50', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1860', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
