(1863, 5, '2011-10-18 16:08:14', '2011-10-18 16:08:14', 'Mr. Wang is a Managing Associate with Futurestep, specialising in strategic talent acquisition in the Industrial Practice for Greater China and is based in Beijing. \r\n\r\nFor the past five years, Mr. Wang has been specialising in the following industrial sectors, Power Generation (Thermal, Hydro, Wind, Solar, Nuclear), Power T&D, Oil & gas, Petrochemical, Chemical, Flow Control, Automation & Drive, HVAC, Construction and Pharmaceutical.\r\n\r\nMr. Wang has fulfilled about 100 search assignments and served over 30 International clients, such as Fortune Global 500 or global leaders in the industrial market. The positions he filled cover a wide range of functions on different levels, from engineers, supervisors, managers, senior managers to directors, GMs, Country heads and Regional leaders. His professional service has been well recognised by his clients and his reputation is built on evaluating how candidates’ qualifications can fill employer requirements and creating a win-win situation for all parties.\r\n\r\nMr. Wang joined Futurestep in 2008 from another global executive search firm based in China where he was a Business Consultant.  \r\n\r\nPrior to joining the search business, he worked as a business associate with a well known State-owned-corporation – China Light Group; where he handled sales and export of over US$1 million worth of outdoor and functional garments into the EU, UK and US markets and developed his commitment and skills to understand and fulfil customers’ needs.  \r\n\r\nMr. Wang is a Chinese native and a Beijing resident. He holds a Bachelor’s Degree of Arts, with a double major in English Literature & International Business from Beijing Foreign Studies University. He speaks fluent Mandarin and English. ', 'Raymond Wang', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'raymond-wang', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:08:14', '2011-10-18 16:08:14', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1863', 0, 'experts', '', 0);
