(1865, 5, '2011-10-18 16:15:12', '2011-10-18 16:15:12', 'Ms. Lee is a Managing Associate with Futurestep, based in Shanghai.\r\n\r\nJoining Futurestep in 2006, Ms. Lee has combined her medical and sales experience with her executive search background to support the life sciences practice. She has been instrumental in the strategic talent acquisition in the various sectors of the healthcare industry. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Lee worked at Career International Co. in Beijing and Shanghai for over two years, where she conducted several high profile placements and many middle-level assignments including some projects in the life sciences sector. \r\n \r\nBefore that she worked with MSD Pharmaceutical Co. and Chrion Limited as a clinical researcher and in sales. She began her career as a physician at Beijing Dongzhimen hospital. \r\n\r\nMs. Lee holds a Master’s degree from the Beijing University of Traditional Chinese Medicine.\r\n', 'Carly Lee ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'carly-lee', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:15:12', '2011-10-18 16:15:12', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1865', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1866, 5, '2011-10-18 16:10:33', '2011-10-18 16:10:33', 'Ms. Lee is a Managing Associate with Futurestep, based in Shanghai.\n\nJoining Futurestep in 2006, Ms. Lee has combined her medical and sales experience with her executive search background to support the life sciences practice. She has been instrumental in the strategic talent acquisition in the various sectors of the healthcare industry. \n\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Ms. Lee worked at Career International Co. in Beijing and Shanghai for over two years, where she conducted several high profile placements and many middle-level assignments including some projects in the life sciences sector. \n \nBefore that she worked with MSD Pharmaceutical Co. and Chrion Limited as a clinical researcher and in sales. She began her career as a physician at Beijing Dongzhimen hospital. \n\nMs. Lee holds a Master’s degree from the Beijing University of Traditional Chinese Medicine.\n', 'Carly Lee ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1865-revision', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:10:33', '2011-10-18 16:10:33', '', 1865, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1867, 5, '2011-10-18 16:24:47', '2011-10-18 16:24:47', 'Mr. Luro is the Market Leader for Futurestep Beijing. He was previously the Industrial Market Leader for Greater China and specialises in strategic talent acquisition for multi-nationals companies.\r\n\r\nFor almost ten years, he has led the roll-out of nearly 200 search assignments in various areas, with a particular emphasis on the Industrial sector and most recently in the Supply Chain Management and Heavy Equipments space. Since the inception, he has been able to build his esteem through high quality execution and consistent consultative approach to his customers. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep in 2007, Mr. Luro was a senior business consultant for one of China’s largest international executive search firms where he was their Industrial specialist. There, he led his team to successfully complete strategic placements for some leading American and European Industrial players. He developed numerous long-term partnerships by maintaining a high level of client satisfaction and assisting them with their talent acquisition strategy. \r\n\r\nPrior to that, Mr. Luro managed the Beijing branch of a local recruitment company for two years. During his tenure he helped the firm to standardise its recruitment process, designed new marketing and recruiting tools, set-up a training plan for new staff, developed new accounts and manage the overall execution of projects. \r\n\r\nMr. Luro holds a post-graduate degree in Human Resources and dual bachelor degree in Administration, Economics and Business Management from the University of Bordeaux Montesquieu.  \r\n\r\nHe is fluent in French and English and is also conversant in Spanish and Chinese.\r\n', 'Bryan Luro', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bryan-luro', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:24:47', '2011-10-18 16:24:47', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1867', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
