(1869, 5, '2011-10-18 16:31:01', '2011-10-18 16:31:01', 'Mr. Wu joined Futurestep in July 2009 as Director of the Search Business in China. He is responsible for professional talent acquisition across all industry sectors and is based in Shanghai.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Wu has been in the recruitment industry for about seven and half years working with two global recruitment firms. \r\n\r\nIn his previous China-based positions, he was responsible for the Chemical, Oil & Gas, Energy & Utility, Property & Construction, and Automotive & Transportation sectors. He also held various leadership roles for both the Operation and Corporate Finance function. Mr. Wu’s significant achievements include expanding businesses in twelve provinces in China and opening the first global recruitment office in Xian, Chongqing and Wuhan. \r\n\r\nA Canadian, Mr. Wu has worked in Asia since 2004, first as Regional Finance Manager for Asia, responsible for overseeing the finance function of nine countries and territories, including China, India, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Philippines, Korea, Taiwan and Hong Kong.\r\n\r\nFrom March to October 2005, Mr. Wu was fully involved in one of the largest acquisition projects in India’s recruitment history. In early 2006, Mr. Wu worked in Singapore as Business Manager of permanent recruitment services. In the same year, he was assigned additional responsibility to manage professional recruitment operations in Malaysia. \r\n\r\nPrior to his transfer to Asia, Mr. Wu has worked in Canada and the U.S. for 16 years for several large global companies, including American Standard, ShawCorp Ltd. and R.R. Donnelly, all in the finance department. Born in Shanghai, Mr. Wu went to Canada to pursue his studies. He speaks fluent English, Mandarin, Cantonese and Shanghai dialect.\r\n\r\nMr. Wu holds a Bachelor of Accounting Science degree from the University of Calgary, Canada. He is a member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA) and a member of the Certified General Accountants (CGA) of Canada.\r\n', 'David Wu', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'david-wu', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:31:01', '2011-10-18 16:31:01', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1869', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
