(1871, 5, '2011-10-18 16:36:19', '2011-10-18 16:36:19', 'Mr. Tay is based in Shanghai and he is responsible for designing strategies and methodologies for various strategic talent acquisition solutions as well as leading the delivery of Outsourced Recruitment and Consulting Solutions for clients in North Asia. Prior to his current role, Mr.Tay was the Market Leader for Futurestep’s Technology/ Professional Services Practice in China.\r\n\r\nBefore relocating to Shanghai, Mr. Tay spent six years in Japan.  Based in Tokyo, he was responsible for business development for the Futurestep Tokyo office as well as solution design, account management and service delivery. \r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, he spent over six years in an international executive search firm. During this period, he worked with clients in different industries including Technology, Real Estate, Telecommunications, Professional Services, Consumer/Retail and Industrial. He has filled various Sales, Marketing, Human Resources, Finance, Operations and Technical roles at middle and senior management level. \r\n\r\nHe was also appointed the key account manager for a major client in Japan where he successfully led the pitch, project management and delivery of a management assessment project as well as two large scale recruitment projects. \r\n\r\nMr. Tay’s career began as an Analyst with an American investment bank in Australia, specialising in risk management and special projects. \r\n\r\nWith his experience in project management, solution design and service delivery - as well as market knowledge of Greater China, Japan, Singapore and Australia - he brings extensive expertise in providing value-added consulting advice to clients from different industries across the region. \r\n\r\nHe graduated from the Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology with a Bachelor of Business (double major in Management & Marketing) and has successfully completed the IPS Planning & Managing Projects course, recognised by the Project Management Institute. \r\n\r\n', 'Jasen Tay ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jasen-tay', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:36:19', '2011-10-18 16:36:19', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1871', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
