(1873, 5, '2011-10-18 16:41:43', '2011-10-18 16:41:43', 'Ms. Jin is a Managing Associate based in the Futurestep Shanghai office focusing primarily on the Information Technology & Telecommunications (IT&T) sector. In this role, she utilises a decade’s worth of project execution, business development and consulting experience in the IT hardware/software and Telecom & Semiconductor sectors.\r\n\r\nHer strengths include in-depth knowledge of the sectors, sound execution skills and communication capabilities and excellent relationships with candidates.\r\n\r\nMs. Jin has been with Futurestep since 2007. She has overall eight years recruiting experience in the industrial sector. Prior to Futurestep she worked for a leading European recruiting firm where she was a High Tech & Industrial Research Associate supporting global mapping projects as well as senior level searches across Asia.\r\n\r\nMs. Jin also worked for a Hong Kong based IT recruitment company for five years, focusing on searches in the IT&T sector for MNCs as well as local Chinese high tech companies.\r\n\r\nEarly in her career, Ms. Jin spent one and a half years with an online recruitment company.\r\n\r\nDuring the past ten years, she has worked with clients from some of worlds leading high-tech companies such as Microsoft, IBM/Lenovo, HP, Apple, SAP, Oracle, EMC, HDS, CA, Phoenix, Mathworks, Lucent, Adobe, Intel, AMD, Marvell and STM. \r\n\r\nMs. Jin was born in Yangzhou city in the Jiangsu Province in China. She graduated from Yangzhou Polytechnic College and speaks Mandarin and English.  \r\n', 'Amy Jin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'amy-jin', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:42:53', '2011-10-18 16:42:53', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1873', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1874, 4, '2011-10-18 16:42:30', '2011-10-18 16:42:30', 'LONDON, March 16, 2011 – Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY),\r\ntoday announced that it has appointed Marisa Kacary as Global Vice President, Marketing. Ms. Kacary has been appointed to lead the company’s marketing programmes and further build Futurestep’s brand as the global leader in strategic talent acquisition solutions.\r\n\r\nBased in London but with a global remit, Ms. Kacary joins Futurestep with considerable industry experience. Most recently, she was Director of Marketing and Communications of Alexander Mann Solutions (AMS), and prior to that, she was responsible for Marketing at Capital Consulting, a leading global pure play RPO provider acquired by AMS in February 2008. Ms. Kacary spent the early part of her career in the IT and telco sector, working in marketing roles for organisations such as Cable&amp;Wireless, Compaq and Nortel Networks.\r\n\r\n“Marisa joins Futurestep at an exciting time," said Byrne Mulrooney, chief executive officer, Futurestep. “As we build on our successes in the global marketplace and execute on our strategic vision, her deep industry experience and marketing communications expertise will ensure that our brand reflects Futurestep’s position as a world-class provider of RPO, consulting and retained search services.”\r\n\r\n“Next to our colleagues, the Korn/Ferry brand is the most valuable asset of our Firm,” said Michael Distefano, senior vice president and chief marketing office, Korn/Ferry. “Marisa makes an excellent addition to the marketing team and will play a significant role as we further transform Korn/Ferry as the premier global provider of talent management solutions.”\r\n\r\nMs. Kacary is a graduate of Durham University with a bachelor’s degree in Geography. She is a member of the Chartered Institute of Marketing (CIM) and holds a CIM Diploma.\r\n\r\nAbout Futurestep\r\n\r\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions;offering fully customized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs.\r\n\r\nOur clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure,proprietary competency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to measure and optimize business impact.\r\n\r\nAs a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements;from RPO and project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class capability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify, attract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.futurestep.com/">www.futurestep.com</a>.\r\n\r\nAbout Korn/Ferry International\r\n\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout theAmericas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East andAfrica, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based inLos Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit http://www.kornferry.com for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and <a href="http://www.kornferryinstitute.com/">http://www.kornferryinstitute.com</a> for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'MARISA KACARY JOINS FUTURESTEP, A KORN/FERRY COMPANY, AS GLOBAL VICE PRESIDENT, MARKETING', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'marisa-kacary-joins-futurestep-a-kornferry-company-as-global-vice-president-marketing', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:42:30', '2011-10-18 16:42:30', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=1874', 0, 'press', '', 0),
