(1879, 5, '2011-10-18 16:45:59', '2011-10-18 16:45:59', 'Mr. Austin is a Consultant based in the Futurestep Shanghai office focusing primarily on the Real Estate, Property and Construction sectors. He is also responsible for developing client relationships in the Life Sciences sector. \r\n\r\nHaving spent the last six years based in Shanghai and Hong Kong within the executive search and recruitment industry, he offers a wealth of experience with regards to talent acquisition strategies across numerous industries in Greater China.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Austin spent three years recruiting primarily within the real estate sector, including spending time with Asia’s leading specialist property and real estate recruitment consultancy. He has assisted with their recruitment strategies and built numerous strong relationships, working closely with owners, investors, developers and consultancies in identifying and attracting high caliber candidates. \r\n\r\nMr. Austin’s career in China commenced with an Asian focused executive search company, covering the major market sectors. As the manager of the Shanghai office, he managed a team of consultants and researchers, ensured continuous growth within the office and built new key accounts whilst increasing the level of service to both clients and candidates.\r\n\r\nA British native, Mr. Austin graduated from Durham University in the UK with a BA in Mandarin and Management Studies. In addition to Mandarin, he has strong German and Dutch language skills.\r\n\r\n', 'Oliver Austin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oliver-austin', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:45:59', '2011-10-18 16:45:59', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1879', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1880, 4, '2011-10-18 16:46:41', '2011-10-18 16:46:41', 'ZURICH, March 3, 2011 – Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY) and leader in strategic talent acquisition solutions, today announced that Benoît Binachon has been appointed Managing Director of Futurestep France. Mr. Binachon has been hired to boost growth and further reinforce the Firm’s consulting offering in France.\r\n\r\nMr. Binachon joins Futurestep with an extensive background in recruitment and professional services. Over the past 15 years, he has built and developed numerous fast growing businesses in management consulting, engineering and recruitment to address the needs of medium to large companies, mainly in France.\r\n\r\nMost recently, he was the Managing Director and co-founder of Business effiScience,a technology-based management consulting firm that employed 40 people across Europe and the United States with a turnover of EUR 10m. Prior to that, he launched and developed Michael Page’s Engineering Consulting business in France, which he grew to 150 employees before the business was sold. Previously, he was an Executive Director of Michael Page International, where he led the Engineering and Technical recruitment department.\r\n\r\n"We are very pleased to add someone of Benoît’s caliber and experience to our leadership team in Europe. Benoît brings to Futurestep significant experience in addressing top-management needs through a consultative approach and tailor-made solutions. He will play an integral role in leading and advancing our strong presence and reputation as an integrated talent management firm in the region," said Joel Perrenoud, President of Futurestep, EMEA.\r\n\r\nAbout Futurestep\r\n\r\nFuturestep is the global industry leader in high-impact recruitment solutions;offering fully customized, flexible services to help organizations meet their talent and recruitment needs.\r\n\r\nOur clients turn to us for proven expertise, a global process and infrastructure,proprietary competency models, innovative sourcing and attraction strategies, and a unique approach to measure and optimize business impact.\r\n\r\nAs a Korn/Ferry Company, Futurestep can meet a variety of workforce requirements;from RPO and project recruitment, to search and consulting, our solutions apply a truly world-class capability to deliver talent with impact, providing the experience and global reach to identify, attract and retain the people who drive business success. To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.futurestep.com/">www.futurestep.com</a>.\r\n\r\nAbout Korn/Ferry International\r\n\r\nKorn/Ferry International, with a presence throughout theAmericas, Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East andAfrica, is a premier global provider of talent management solutions. Based inLos Angeles, the firm delivers an array of solutions that help clients to attract, deploy, develop and reward their talent. Visit http://www.kornferry.com for more information on the Korn/Ferry International family of companies, and http://www.kornferryinstitute.com for thought leadership, intellectual property and research.', 'BENOÎT BINACHON NAMED MANAGING DIRECTOR OF FUTURESTEP FRANCE', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'benoit-binachon-named-managing-director-of-futurestep-france', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:46:41', '2011-10-18 16:46:41', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=1880', 0, 'press', '', 0),
(1881, 5, '2011-10-18 16:44:09', '2011-10-18 16:44:09', 'Mr. Austin is a Consultant based in the Futurestep Shanghai office focusing primarily on the Real Estate, Property and Construction sectors. He is also responsible for developing client relationships in the Life Sciences sector. \n\nHaving spent the last six years based in Shanghai and Hong Kong within the executive search and recruitment industry, he offers a wealth of experience with regards to talent acquisition strategies across numerous industries in Greater China.\n\nPrior to joining Futurestep, Mr. Austin spent three years recruiting primarily within the real estate sector, including spending time with Asia’s leading specialist property and real estate recruitment consultancy. He has assisted with their recruitment strategies and built numerous strong relationships, working closely with owners, investors, developers and consultancies in identifying and attracting high caliber candidates. \n\nMr. Austin’s career in China commenced with an Asian focused executive search company, covering the major market sectors. As the manager of the Shanghai office, he managed a team of consultants and researchers, ensured continuous growth within the office and built new key accounts whilst increasing the level of service to both clients and candidates.\n\nA British native, Mr. Austin graduated from Durham University in the UK with a BA in Mandarin and Management Studies. In addition to Mandarin, he has strong German and Dutch language skills.\n\n', 'Oliver Austin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1879-revision', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:44:09', '2011-10-18 16:44:09', '', 1879, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1882, 5, '2011-10-18 16:49:02', '2011-10-18 16:49:02', 'Currently based in Shanghai, Ms. Wong is the Market Leader for the Consumer & Retail practice and is responsible for the Greater China Region. In this role, she leverages a decade’s worth of business development, marketing and consulting experience in the consumer & retail sector.   \r\n\r\nCurrently leading a team of members situated across offices in China; Ms. Wong is seasoned in designing customised recruitment solution for international companies/luxury brands within Greater China region.  \r\n\r\nBefore joining Futurestep, Ms. Wong was the Managing Consultant at a leading US Recruitment Company where she was responsible for developing new business.\r\n\r\nPrior to that, Ms. Wong spent a number of years as a Business Development Manager at Paul, Hastings, Janofsky & Walker LLP, an international law firm where her role involved in strategic planning and client relationship management.  \r\n\r\nHer earlier career involved in marketing consumer products for the North Asia region where she focused on channel development and managed a yearly budget of USD60 million.\r\n\r\nMs. Wong was born in Shanghai and grew up in Hong Kong. Educated at Hong Kong International School, she received her Bachelor degree in Business Administration from University of Victoria, British Columbia.  Ms. Wong also speaks fluent English, Cantonese, Mandarin and Shanghai dialect. \r\n', 'Jane Wong', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jane-wong', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:49:02', '2011-10-18 16:49:02', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=experts&#038;p=1882', 0, 'experts', '', 0),
(1883, 4, '2011-10-18 16:45:25', '2011-10-18 16:45:25', 'ZURICH, March 3, 2011 – Futurestep, a Korn/Ferry company (NYSE:KFY) and\nleader in strategic talent acquisition solutions, today announced that Benoît Binachon has been appointed Managing Director of Futurestep France. Mr. Binachon has been hired to boost growth and further reinforce the Firm’s consulting offering in France.\n\nMr. Binachon joins Futurestep with an extensive background in recruitment and professional services. Over the past 15 years, he has built and developed numerous fast growing businesses in management consulting, engineering and recruitment to address the needs of medium to large companies, mainly in France.\n\nMost recently, he was the Managing Director and co-founder of Business effiScience,a technology-based management consulting firm that employed 40 people across Europe and the United States with a turnover of EUR 10m. Prior to that, he launched and developed Michael Page’s Engineering Consulting business in France, which he grew to 150 employees before the business was sold. Previously, he was an Executive\nDirector of Michael Page International, where he led the Engineering and Technical recruitment department.\n\n"We are very pleased to add someone of Benoît’s caliber and experience to our leadership team in Europe. Benoît brings to Futurestep significant experience in addressing top-management needs through a consultative approach and tailor-made solutions. He will play an integral role in leading and advancing our strong presence and reputation as an integrated talent management firm in the region," said Joel Perrenoud, President of Futurestep, EMEA.', 'BENOÎT BINACHON NAMED MANAGING DIRECTOR OF FUTURESTEP FRANCE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1880-revision', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:45:25', '2011-10-18 16:45:25', '', 1880, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/uncategorized/%sub-category%/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
