(1885, 4, '2011-10-18 16:50:15', '2011-10-18 16:50:15', 'LOS ANGELES, January 19, 2011 – The Newman Group, a Futurestep Company\r\nand leading provider of talent management consulting solutions today announced that Madeline Laurano has joined the organization as Talent Systems Analyst and Advisory Practice Leader.\r\n\r\nIn this role, Ms. Laurano will oversee the continuing development and evolution of the company’s highly regarded talent management technology consulting and thought leadership activity. This includes management of talent systems evaluation and selection services as well as oversight of industry monitoring, research,communications and presentations.\r\n\r\nMs. Laurano joined The Newman Group from Bersin &amp; Associates, where she served as Principal Analyst of Talent Acquisition. Her areas of expertise include workforce planning, sourcing strategies, screening and assessments, RPO, employer branding, onboarding and talent management systems. Prior to joining Bersin, Ms. Laurano served as the Research Director for the Electronic Recruiting Exchange (ERE) Media where she created the ERE webinar series, published the Talent Acquisition Industry Analysis and Buyers Guide, led community discussion groups, and took on leadership and major contributor roles in research projects and development of services. Prior to ERE, she worked as a Research Analyst for the Aberdeen Group and Research Director for Linkage, Inc, where she co-edited Best Practices in Leading a Global Workforce and Secrets in Succession Planning.\r\n\r\n“The Newman Group is known as one of the most reliable resources available today for tackling the toughest decisions related to talent management technology,” said Newman Group General Manager Kelly Cartwright. “As a recognized thought leader in the space, Madeline has a wealth of industry knowledge and experience associated with talent management solutions. Through her leadership, we will continue to provide the deep knowledge and practical insight our clients and colleagues have come to expect when addressing critical technology questions.”\r\n\r\nMs. Laurano is scheduled to present in a number of industry venues in the coming months, including Webinars for the Electronic Recruiting Exchange (ERE) and Social Business Week as well as a conference presentation for International Association for Human Resource Information Management (IHRIM). Also, look for her insight on the Talent Strategy Blog at <a href="http://www.thetalentstrategyblog.com/">http://www.thetalentstrategyblog.com/</a>', 'MADELINE LAURANO JOINS THE NEWMAN GROUP, A FUTURESTEP COMPANY, AS TALENT SYSTEMS ANALYST AND ADVISORY PRACTICE LEADER', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'madeline-laurano-joins-the-newman-group-a-futurestep-company-as-talent-systems-analyst-and-advisory-practice-leader', '', '', '2011-10-18 16:50:15', '2011-10-18 16:50:15', '', 0, 'http://futurestep.testarea.me.uk/?post_type=press&#038;p=1885', 0, 'press', '', 0),
